51
00:00:01,420 --> 00:00:04,298
[♪ Alexi Murdoch: "All My Days"]

2
00:02:26,773 --> 00:02:29,776
[crowd screaming]

3
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,142
[phone ringing]

4
00:03:05,562 --> 00:03:07,939
[grunting]

5
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,568
[groans]

6
00:03:11,735 --> 00:03:13,111
Hang on, hang on, hang on.

7
00:03:13,278 --> 00:03:15,405
- [ringing continues]
- Come on.

8
00:03:15,572 --> 00:03:17,866
- Yeah?
<i>- [man] Where are you, Charlie?</i>

9
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:19,826
<i>More importantly, where is my money?</i>

10
00:03:19,993 --> 00:03:21,411
<i>- You're into me for 30 grand.</i>
- All right, all right.

11
00:03:21,578 --> 00:03:23,705
Jack, Jack, Jack,
I'm going to pay you.

12
00:03:23,872 --> 00:03:25,707
<i>This ain't Jack! It's Bill Panner.</i>

13
00:03:25,874 --> 00:03:27,417
<i>You owe Jack money, too?</i>

14
00:03:27,584 --> 00:03:29,419
<i>Charlie, you pay me first!</i>

15
00:03:29,586 --> 00:03:31,713
Bill, hey, no, we're good, buddy.

16
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,215
I got your money.
It's right here in my hand.

17
00:03:33,381 --> 00:03:38,053
So why don't we meet up on the...
[stammering]

18
00:03:41,014 --> 00:03:42,516
<i>- Charlie, your phone's going screwy.</i>
- Bill?

19
00:03:42,682 --> 00:03:43,892
<i>- Hello?</i>
- I'm losing you, Bill.

20
00:03:44,059 --> 00:03:46,645
<i>Wait, Charlie,</i>
<i>I can't hear what you're saying.</i>

21
00:03:48,980 --> 00:03:52,150
[girl] Hey, mister.
Is that Ambush?

22
00:03:52,317 --> 00:03:55,612
- Uh, yeah.
- Can we see him?

23
00:03:57,197 --> 00:03:59,241
- You want to see him?
- Yeah.

24
00:03:59,407 --> 00:04:03,161
All right, give me...
Give me a minute.

25
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,460
This...

26
00:04:10,627 --> 00:04:13,421
...is Ambush. Wakey, wakey.

27
00:04:14,381 --> 00:04:16,466
- [beeping]
- [whirrs]

28
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:17,634
[gasps]

29
00:04:33,483 --> 00:04:36,528
- What robot is he fighting?
- Actually, he's going to fight...

30
00:04:36,695 --> 00:04:38,363
Whoa, little lady.
What are you doing?

31
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:41,575
- Can we get a picture with him?
- Sure. For five dollars.

32
00:04:41,741 --> 00:04:43,869
You want five dollars? Seriously?

33
00:04:44,035 --> 00:04:46,538
No, I want five dollars immediately.

34
00:04:46,705 --> 00:04:48,248
Come on, guys.

35
00:04:48,415 --> 00:04:49,958
Hey, hey.

36
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:51,543
All right, all right, I'm kidding.

37
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:53,253
- Three bucks.
- Whatever.

38
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:55,922
- How about $2.50?
- [girl] You suck!

39
00:04:57,174 --> 00:04:59,009
All right.

40
00:04:59,176 --> 00:05:02,554
It's going to be one
of those towns, huh?

41
00:05:02,721 --> 00:05:04,681
<i>[announcer] Welcome,</i>
<i>ladies and gentlemen,</i>

42
00:05:04,848 --> 00:05:07,142
<i>to the 2020 San Leandro County Fair.</i>

43
00:05:07,309 --> 00:05:08,268
- Yah!
<i>- Please take your seats.</i>

44
00:05:08,435 --> 00:05:11,229
<i>We're almost ready</i>
<i>to get this thing stared.</i>

45
00:05:11,396 --> 00:05:13,231
[grunts]

46
00:05:13,398 --> 00:05:15,901
I was told my bot
was fighting an 800-pound steer.

47
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,570
Hey, hey!
That is not 800 pounds, knucklehead.

48
00:05:18,737 --> 00:05:22,032
[man] Charlie "the Can Do Kid" Kenton.

49
00:05:22,199 --> 00:05:23,783
Time has not
been good to you, my friend.

50
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,619
Ricky, we got a problem here.
A big problem.

51
00:05:25,785 --> 00:05:28,455
Whoa, hey, slow down there, hoss.

52
00:05:28,622 --> 00:05:30,332
Come on, last time I saw you,

53
00:05:30,498 --> 00:05:33,084
you were staring up at the ceiling
at the Sam Houston Center

54
00:05:33,251 --> 00:05:35,545
with the taste of my right cross
all over your face.

55
00:05:35,712 --> 00:05:37,714
Pow!

56
00:05:37,881 --> 00:05:40,008
- Are we good to go here?
- Yeah.

57
00:05:40,175 --> 00:05:43,595
We agreed that my boxer would fight
an 800-pound steer for three grand.

58
00:05:43,762 --> 00:05:45,388
- Am I right?
- Yes, sir. We did.

59
00:05:45,555 --> 00:05:47,515
- That bull is, like, 2,000 pounds.
- Right, OK.

60
00:05:47,682 --> 00:05:49,392
Well, Charlie, I'll tell you something.

61
00:05:49,559 --> 00:05:52,562
Your bot don't fight,
you don't get paid! Whoo!

62
00:05:52,729 --> 00:05:54,439
- How about that?
- [man chuckles]

63
00:05:55,482 --> 00:05:57,984
- Get the hell out of here.
- [bull groans]

64
00:05:58,151 --> 00:06:00,195
All right, all right.

65
00:06:01,488 --> 00:06:02,906
Why don't we
make this more interesting?

66
00:06:03,073 --> 00:06:04,783
My bot against your bull, straight up.

67
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,743
- How much?
- Twenty grand, winner takes all.

68
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:09,704
- You got 20 grand, Charlie?
- In a safe in my truck.

69
00:06:13,291 --> 00:06:15,252
All right, Charlie.
I'll tell you what,

70
00:06:15,418 --> 00:06:18,672
twenty grand it is,
but if you lose and you welch,

71
00:06:18,838 --> 00:06:21,508
I'm gonna come after you and beat you
to within an inch of your life.

72
00:06:21,675 --> 00:06:23,843
And you know that I can do that
because I already done done it!

73
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:25,470
What's the problem with you, man?
In life you get too close,

74
00:06:25,637 --> 00:06:27,597
in the ring you
stand back like a girl. Just shake.

75
00:06:27,764 --> 00:06:29,307
All right, Charlie.

76
00:06:29,474 --> 00:06:31,017
Shake and pow!
Just like that once again.

77
00:06:31,184 --> 00:06:33,019
You want to dance again?
You wanna dance?

78
00:06:33,186 --> 00:06:34,604
Come on, cheer for this guy.
Give him some luck.

79
00:06:34,771 --> 00:06:36,564
He needs some luck, y'all.
Yahoo! Let's get going!

80
00:06:36,731 --> 00:06:40,193
- [bull groans]
- Don't touch that bull.

81
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,862
Ladies and gentlemen, I got to ask,

82
00:06:43,029 --> 00:06:45,282
do we have any fans
of robot boxing here today?

83
00:06:45,448 --> 00:06:47,409
- [cheering]
- [Ricky chuckles]

84
00:06:47,575 --> 00:06:50,245
Now, listen, friends, I understand,

85
00:06:50,412 --> 00:06:54,165
we can't all afford to go all
the way over there to Dallas

86
00:06:54,332 --> 00:06:59,212
and pay $300 for one of those World
Robot Boxing League fights. I get it.

87
00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:02,465
So, I decided that I would
bring a robot boxing match

88
00:07:02,632 --> 00:07:06,052
right here to our little fair
here in San Leandro.

89
00:07:06,219 --> 00:07:08,138
How about that?

90
00:07:08,305 --> 00:07:09,806
All right.

91
00:07:11,057 --> 00:07:13,893
Ladies and gentlemen,
I introduce to you,

92
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:18,773
- Ambush!
- Let's do it!

93
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:21,151
[metal music playing]

94
00:07:21,318 --> 00:07:22,902
All right, big fella.

95
00:07:26,698 --> 00:07:28,366
[Ricky] Whoo-hoo!

96
00:07:28,533 --> 00:07:30,327
He's a big fella, ain't he?

97
00:07:30,493 --> 00:07:33,997
Take a turn.
Let them see how beautiful you are.

98
00:07:35,498 --> 00:07:37,250
Yeah.

99
00:07:37,417 --> 00:07:39,753
[chuckles] Show them some power.

100
00:07:41,004 --> 00:07:43,631
[Ricky] Look at that.
He's getting all kung fu-y on us.

101
00:07:43,798 --> 00:07:47,135
- Yeah!
- [Ricky] Yeah, big fella.

102
00:07:47,302 --> 00:07:49,554
Ambush's opponent today,
he's last year's runner-up

103
00:07:49,721 --> 00:07:51,765
in the baddest
of the bulls competition,

104
00:07:51,931 --> 00:07:57,395
ladies and gentlemen, Black Thunder!

105
00:07:57,562 --> 00:07:59,731
[crowd roars]

106
00:07:59,898 --> 00:08:01,524
- Let's get it on!
- Let's get this thing started.

107
00:08:01,691 --> 00:08:04,402
- [grunts]
- [whirring]

108
00:08:05,236 --> 00:08:06,654
Is that all you got?

109
00:08:08,448 --> 00:08:10,700
Yeah, brother. Bring it on.

110
00:08:20,835 --> 00:08:22,212
Take him, take him.

111
00:08:24,631 --> 00:08:27,133
Ambush lays the smackdown
on that prime beef.

112
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,426
Woo woo!

113
00:08:33,098 --> 00:08:35,183
I got more for you, big fella.
We're just getting started.

114
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,146
OK. Jump, now!

115
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:45,068
Boo-yah!

116
00:08:48,196 --> 00:08:49,406
- Dang it!
- [Ricky] Ambush, decks

117
00:08:49,572 --> 00:08:51,449
Black Thunder
but when you mess with the bull,

118
00:08:51,616 --> 00:08:53,284
you're going to get the horns.

119
00:08:56,037 --> 00:08:57,580
You like that. I can tell.

120
00:08:57,747 --> 00:08:59,541
- You like that.
- [bull grunting]

121
00:08:59,707 --> 00:09:00,834
Jeez! Turn around!

122
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,088
[mechanical chirping]

123
00:09:05,255 --> 00:09:07,715
Ricky! Ricky, stop this thing!

124
00:09:13,263 --> 00:09:14,556
[crowd gasps]

125
00:09:14,722 --> 00:09:17,851
[cheering]

126
00:09:18,017 --> 00:09:19,394
Come on, come on.
We're still in this thing.

127
00:09:19,561 --> 00:09:20,854
We're still in this. Just hop. Hop.

128
00:09:22,188 --> 00:09:23,398
That's it. Come on.

129
00:09:27,527 --> 00:09:29,946
Ricky, enough! Enough!

130
00:09:30,113 --> 00:09:33,241
I can't hear you over the sound
of your robot being destroyed.

131
00:09:33,408 --> 00:09:34,534
[laughing]

132
00:09:34,701 --> 00:09:37,495
[chanting] Kill! Kill! Kill!

133
00:09:37,662 --> 00:09:39,456
All right, come on. Get up.

134
00:09:40,415 --> 00:09:42,876
Get up. Come on!

135
00:09:44,502 --> 00:09:45,962
[groans] No!

136
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:53,219
C'mon. No, no, no!

137
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:01,102
[Ricky] Ladies and gentlemen,
let's hear it

138
00:10:01,269 --> 00:10:05,732
for our warriors out here today
at the 2020 San Leandro County Fair.

139
00:10:05,899 --> 00:10:07,817
Now, thank you all for coming out,

140
00:10:07,984 --> 00:10:11,237
and we'll see you next time,
because there will be one.

141
00:10:11,404 --> 00:10:13,698
Hey, hey! Give me that leg.

142
00:10:13,865 --> 00:10:15,700
Sure. For five dollars.

143
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,535
Boo-yah!

144
00:10:17,702 --> 00:10:20,288
Whoo! All right!

145
00:10:20,455 --> 00:10:24,542
That was ridonculous fun,
now wasn't it, ladies and gentlemen?

146
00:10:25,376 --> 00:10:28,671
I'm going to come by for my money,
Charlie boy. You best have it.

147
00:10:28,838 --> 00:10:30,840
- Everybody say "hey!"
- [audience] Hey!

148
00:10:31,007 --> 00:10:34,719
- Everybody say "ho!"
- [audience] Ho!

149
00:10:34,886 --> 00:10:38,139
How about that?
How you doing there, little robot?

150
00:10:54,822 --> 00:10:57,242
[muttering] My keys, damn it.

151
00:10:57,408 --> 00:10:59,410
One more step
and I'll drop you like your girlfriend.

152
00:10:59,577 --> 00:11:00,828
Charlie, relax.

153
00:11:00,995 --> 00:11:02,539
I'm not paying you.
That was a bogus fight.

154
00:11:02,705 --> 00:11:04,791
- It cost me my last robot.
- Just listen to us.

155
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:08,419
- Do you recall Caroline Fallon?
- She's my ex-girlfriend.

156
00:11:08,586 --> 00:11:11,089
I haven't seen her in like ten years.
What does she want?

157
00:11:11,256 --> 00:11:14,634
- Nothing. She died.
- Do you recall Max Kenton?

158
00:11:16,469 --> 00:11:18,096
He's my son.
He's got to be like nine.

159
00:11:18,263 --> 00:11:19,931
- Eleven.
- Eleven. OK.

160
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:22,850
[sighs] Is he dead, too?

161
00:11:23,017 --> 00:11:25,853
No, he's fine.
That's why we're here.

162
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:28,523
[soft music playing]

163
00:11:52,171 --> 00:11:55,800
[man] This court is convened
to address the custodial status

164
00:11:55,967 --> 00:11:59,012
of one Max Kenton, age 11.

165
00:11:59,178 --> 00:12:01,097
Mother, Caroline Fallon, deceased.

166
00:12:01,264 --> 00:12:02,890
Father, Charles Kenton.

167
00:12:03,057 --> 00:12:05,101
Debra Fallon Barnes,
you're the boy's aunt.

168
00:12:05,268 --> 00:12:08,730
Yes. As I've already told you,

169
00:12:08,896 --> 00:12:10,857
my husband, Marvin, is wealthy,

170
00:12:11,024 --> 00:12:14,193
and we can more than provide for Max.

171
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:17,989
I appreciate that, but per Texas
state law, without a written will

172
00:12:18,156 --> 00:12:19,741
next of kin retains custody.

173
00:12:19,907 --> 00:12:22,952
Charles Kenton, who is aware
of this custody hearing,

174
00:12:23,119 --> 00:12:24,621
and we are expecting him...

175
00:12:24,787 --> 00:12:27,290
[Charlie] No, I need a new robot now.

176
00:12:27,457 --> 00:12:29,626
I had a big fight
for Ambush next Saturday.

177
00:12:29,792 --> 00:12:31,294
I got to show up with something.

178
00:12:31,461 --> 00:12:33,546
Noisy Boy is for sale?

179
00:12:33,713 --> 00:12:37,216
In his day, Noisy Boy was a killer.
How much?

180
00:12:37,383 --> 00:12:39,552
That's a good deal.
What's wrong with him?

181
00:12:39,719 --> 00:12:41,638
I can live with that.

182
00:12:43,014 --> 00:12:44,182
Well, I don't have it have it.

183
00:12:44,349 --> 00:12:47,060
Charles Kenton waived all
of his rights to custody

184
00:12:47,226 --> 00:12:51,064
right after the boy was born.
I can more than provide for Max.

185
00:12:51,939 --> 00:12:53,274
Whoa.

186
00:12:53,441 --> 00:12:54,692
Please be Charles Kenton.

187
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:58,404
Uh... Charlie, yeah.

188
00:12:58,571 --> 00:13:01,491
[stammers] I'm here to sign some paper

189
00:13:01,658 --> 00:13:04,952
that releases my rights
to the custody of my son.

190
00:13:05,119 --> 00:13:07,038
That's why I'm here.
Do I need to be here?

191
00:13:07,205 --> 00:13:09,457
Charlie.

192
00:13:09,624 --> 00:13:12,168
Do you even remember me?

193
00:13:12,335 --> 00:13:14,879
- Debra, Caroline's sister.
- Yeah, sure, Debra. How are you?

194
00:13:15,046 --> 00:13:16,047
- Mr Kenton.
- Yeah.

195
00:13:16,214 --> 00:13:17,256
Please take a seat.

196
00:13:19,884 --> 00:13:22,512
Your Honor, may I please go
and see my nephew now?

197
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:24,013
Yes, you may.

198
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:26,391
- How about you, Mr Kenton?
- What?

199
00:13:26,557 --> 00:13:28,559
You can spend some time with him,
if you'd like.

200
00:13:28,726 --> 00:13:30,353
- With the kid?
- [Debra] Yeah, the kid.

201
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,313
- Max. Your son?
- All right, all right.

202
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,233
You've been working with those robots
for so long, you've become one.

203
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,653
Honey, you wait right here.
I'm going to be back.

204
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:41,447
You take all the time you need,
sweetheart.

205
00:13:46,869 --> 00:13:50,081
Your Honor,
I'd like to, at this juncture,

206
00:13:50,248 --> 00:13:52,959
step out and call my attorney,
if that's all right.

207
00:13:53,126 --> 00:13:54,419
[judge] Please.

208
00:13:57,797 --> 00:14:00,550
Come on. Come on.

209
00:14:00,717 --> 00:14:02,593
There you are.

210
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:05,179
He'll be in a foster home.

211
00:14:05,346 --> 00:14:08,182
No, they find good families.

212
00:14:08,349 --> 00:14:10,017
Young, energetic. Yeah.

213
00:14:11,269 --> 00:14:14,230
Thanks, Michael. I will. OK.

214
00:14:14,397 --> 00:14:15,565
- [phone beeps]
- Oh, hey.

215
00:14:15,732 --> 00:14:17,692
Hey, um...

216
00:14:17,859 --> 00:14:20,903
- Marvin Barnes. I'm Debra's husband.
- Right, yeah.

217
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:23,865
You know,
Debra really wants to adopt Max.

218
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:26,451
And...

219
00:14:26,617 --> 00:14:29,620
- I'm up for it, but...
- Seventy-five grand.

220
00:14:30,455 --> 00:14:31,748
$75,000?

221
00:14:31,914 --> 00:14:35,126
- You're serious?
- Mm-hmm.

222
00:14:36,961 --> 00:14:38,463
The thing is...

223
00:14:39,338 --> 00:14:41,090
...we're supposed to go
to Italy this summer

224
00:14:41,257 --> 00:14:44,927
with my oldest friend and his wife.
Two months in Tuscany and all over.

225
00:14:45,094 --> 00:14:46,596
Just the four of you. Sounds nice.

226
00:14:46,763 --> 00:14:49,974
We'll be back in New York
by the end of August.

227
00:14:50,141 --> 00:14:53,269
In August. A hundred.

228
00:14:53,436 --> 00:14:55,354
- $100,000?
- You heard me.

229
00:14:55,521 --> 00:14:57,774
- You're crazy.
- Not nearly as crazy as your wife

230
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:01,194
if you tell her I just signed
over that kid to the state of Texas.

231
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:04,989
The way I see it, there's a real way
everyone gets what they want here.

232
00:15:05,156 --> 00:15:07,283
So here's what you're going to do.

233
00:15:07,450 --> 00:15:10,328
You're going to tell your wife
I'll only sign over custody to her

234
00:15:10,495 --> 00:15:12,789
if I get to spend the summer
with the kid first.

235
00:15:12,955 --> 00:15:15,374
Just tell her how guilty
she made me feel

236
00:15:15,541 --> 00:15:19,545
for being such a terrible absentee dad
how I want to make good with junior,

237
00:15:19,712 --> 00:15:21,714
a little fatherly bonding, whatnot.

238
00:15:21,881 --> 00:15:26,177
She'll buy it, you get to be the hero,
and everybody wins.

239
00:15:29,096 --> 00:15:32,892
OK. But not a word about the money
to Debra, you understand?

240
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:35,269
I understand.

241
00:15:35,436 --> 00:15:37,814
I'll give you 50 grand tonight
when we drop off Max

242
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:39,982
and the other 50
when we get back in August

243
00:15:40,149 --> 00:15:42,235
and you deliver him to us in New York.

244
00:15:42,401 --> 00:15:44,612
Pleasure doing business with you.

245
00:15:47,323 --> 00:15:49,700
Your Honor, I'm really happy
we all took the time

246
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:51,410
to make the best decision for everyone.

247
00:15:54,664 --> 00:15:56,332
- Happy?
- [Charlie] Yeah, it's me.

248
00:15:56,499 --> 00:15:59,502
I'm buying Noisy Boy.
I got the money.

249
00:15:59,669 --> 00:16:02,839
Take him to Tallet's Gym
and I'll meet you there.

250
00:16:17,645 --> 00:16:18,646
Hello?

251
00:16:19,856 --> 00:16:21,274
Bailey?

252
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,067
Some guy is here
with the robot you're buying,

253
00:16:23,234 --> 00:16:24,360
and I gotta tell ya, Charlie,

254
00:16:24,527 --> 00:16:27,280
- it smells like disaster to me.
- Nice to see you, too, Bailey.

255
00:16:27,446 --> 00:16:30,408
- Might I also say how cute you look.
- Give it up, Charlie.

256
00:16:30,575 --> 00:16:32,493
God, I need a shower.
You want to take a shower?

257
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:35,538
- Come on.
- Let me make something clear.

258
00:16:35,705 --> 00:16:38,541
A creepy dude with a robot in a box

259
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:41,085
has been sitting outside my gym
for two hours.

260
00:16:41,252 --> 00:16:43,379
Now, putting aside the fact
that you're doing

261
00:16:43,546 --> 00:16:46,132
what I'm guessing is a black market deal
on my doorstep,

262
00:16:46,299 --> 00:16:48,217
how are you gonna pay him
when Ambush just got destroyed?

263
00:16:48,384 --> 00:16:50,553
The money is on its way.
Just, you know, distract him.

264
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,597
- I have been. It's exhausting.
- You're the best.

265
00:16:52,763 --> 00:16:53,848
- Yeah? Really?
- Mm-hmm.

266
00:16:54,015 --> 00:16:55,975
Is that why
you're buying a $45,000 robot

267
00:16:56,142 --> 00:16:57,143
when you owe me six grand in rent?

268
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:58,269
- Because I'm the best?
- Three.

269
00:16:58,436 --> 00:16:59,562
- No, six.
- Whoa.

270
00:16:59,729 --> 00:17:03,691
No, listen, Charlie. There is a guy with
real money who wants to buy this place.

271
00:17:03,858 --> 00:17:06,027
Come on, like you're really
going to sell your dad's gym.

272
00:17:06,193 --> 00:17:07,778
If you don't make rent,
I can't make payments

273
00:17:07,945 --> 00:17:09,280
and I won't have a choice.

274
00:17:09,447 --> 00:17:11,365
Your father would climb out of his grave
and kick your ass

275
00:17:11,532 --> 00:17:13,117
- if you sold this place.
- My father would climb out of his grave

276
00:17:13,284 --> 00:17:15,077
and kick your ass.

277
00:17:15,244 --> 00:17:16,245
[sighs]

278
00:17:17,455 --> 00:17:19,582
Bailey.

279
00:17:24,086 --> 00:17:25,504
- Don't.
- Don't what?

280
00:17:25,671 --> 00:17:27,298
Don't do that. Don't... that...

281
00:17:27,465 --> 00:17:29,091
Hey.

282
00:17:29,258 --> 00:17:31,218
- Don't what?
- Don't do that thing.

283
00:17:33,971 --> 00:17:35,681
- No, you like that thing.
- No.

284
00:17:35,848 --> 00:17:37,975
- Yeah.
- No, I don't like that thing.

285
00:17:38,142 --> 00:17:40,061
I used to. Once. Briefly.

286
00:17:40,227 --> 00:17:42,063
Now I like money more.

287
00:17:42,813 --> 00:17:45,942
- I don't believe you.
- I don't care.

288
00:17:46,108 --> 00:17:47,568
[clears throat]

289
00:17:47,735 --> 00:17:49,612
Marvin.

290
00:17:50,655 --> 00:17:51,906
Your money has arrived.

291
00:17:54,283 --> 00:17:55,910
Marv.

292
00:17:59,997 --> 00:18:02,875
Fifty grand, as promised.

293
00:18:03,042 --> 00:18:06,003
- Now, here are all our numbers
- Right.

294
00:18:06,170 --> 00:18:08,464
- and contact info over in Europe.
- All right.

295
00:18:08,631 --> 00:18:10,049
So that's everything there.

296
00:18:13,344 --> 00:18:16,097
So Marvin tells me you want
this time with Max.

297
00:18:16,263 --> 00:18:18,474
- Yeah, yeah.
- You did the right thing

298
00:18:18,641 --> 00:18:21,143
giving me custody. I think
Caroline would have wanted that.

299
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:22,770
Yeah.

300
00:18:22,937 --> 00:18:25,272
Now, have him back in New York
on August 27th.

301
00:18:26,524 --> 00:18:27,650
That's a deal.

302
00:18:27,817 --> 00:18:30,820
- OK, well, let's go get Max.
- OK.

303
00:18:30,987 --> 00:18:33,656
OK? Let's get Max.

304
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:39,286
It's OK. You want me to go on the
other side here and I'll get Max?

305
00:18:40,287 --> 00:18:42,873
Hey, Max.

306
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:45,251
See you, pal.

307
00:18:45,418 --> 00:18:47,962
[Debra] Max, we'll see you
at the end of the summer, honey.

308
00:18:57,805 --> 00:18:59,140
I'm Charlie.

309
00:19:03,644 --> 00:19:05,855
It's been a long time.
You know, I'm your...

310
00:19:06,022 --> 00:19:08,065
- You screwed me.
- Nice mouth.

311
00:19:08,232 --> 00:19:09,275
Do you know where they're going?

312
00:19:09,442 --> 00:19:11,444
- Italy?
- Yeah, Italy.

313
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:13,654
- So how did I get stuck here with you?
- Relax, kid.

314
00:19:13,821 --> 00:19:16,115
You got a whole life
of fine living ahead of you.

315
00:19:16,282 --> 00:19:19,910
Charlie, dude's pissed.
He's going to take off.

316
00:19:20,077 --> 00:19:22,329
- Yeah, OK.
- Did Marvin give you that money?

317
00:19:22,496 --> 00:19:25,791
Here, just close the deal.
I'll be right there, OK?

318
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,669
- OK?
- Hey.

319
00:19:28,836 --> 00:19:30,129
Hey.

320
00:19:30,296 --> 00:19:33,049
- I'm Bailey.
- Max.

321
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:36,260
Max Kenton.

322
00:19:37,428 --> 00:19:39,263
- Wow, OK, so this is your...
- Yeah, it's him.

323
00:19:39,430 --> 00:19:41,557
Don't worry about it, OK?

324
00:19:41,724 --> 00:19:42,975
I'm standing here looking at you two...

325
00:19:43,142 --> 00:19:46,187
Just go and put Noisy in the shop,
please? Thank you.

326
00:19:47,730 --> 00:19:50,983
[sighs]

327
00:19:52,818 --> 00:19:54,570
So listen, you're going to stay here
with her while I'm on the road.

328
00:19:54,737 --> 00:19:55,988
How much did he give you, huh?

329
00:19:56,155 --> 00:19:58,032
You're coming
at this the wrong way, kid.

330
00:19:58,199 --> 00:19:59,325
No, tell me. I want to know.

331
00:20:00,451 --> 00:20:02,870
50,000. OK?

332
00:20:03,037 --> 00:20:05,164
He gave me $50,000
to sign you over to her.

333
00:20:05,331 --> 00:20:07,249
Will you shut up now?

334
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,626
You sold me?

335
00:20:10,336 --> 00:20:11,378
Sounds worse than it is.

336
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:14,173
- Really.
- It's just to take care of you.

337
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:16,258
Give me half the money
and you won't have to.

338
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:19,261
- Where are you going to go?
- Give me the money. I'll be fine.

339
00:20:19,428 --> 00:20:21,013
I told your aunt I'll get you
to New York at the end of the summer.

340
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:22,723
Now you're concerned for Aunt Debra?

341
00:20:23,599 --> 00:20:26,102
You sold me for 50 grand.
You owe me half!

342
00:20:26,268 --> 00:20:28,145
I don't have it!
I spent the money on a robot.

343
00:20:28,312 --> 00:20:30,523
It's gone! OK? Gone!

344
00:20:30,689 --> 00:20:32,316
I'm through here.

345
00:20:40,491 --> 00:20:41,992
All right, what do we got?

346
00:20:42,993 --> 00:20:45,204
Noisy Boy has arrived.

347
00:20:45,371 --> 00:20:48,082
That's a lot of airline stickers
and customs tags.

348
00:20:48,249 --> 00:20:51,502
- Yep, he's been all over the world.
- London, Japan, Brazil, São Paulo...

349
00:20:51,669 --> 00:20:54,255
Hasn't seen North American soil
in over two years.

350
00:20:54,421 --> 00:20:56,757
Maybe that's why you got such
a good price, genius.

351
00:20:59,468 --> 00:21:02,012
[Charlie] Decided to stay, huh?

352
00:21:02,179 --> 00:21:04,306
This is Bailey. She'll be looking
after you for a few weeks.

353
00:21:04,473 --> 00:21:05,391
- What?
- By the way,

354
00:21:05,558 --> 00:21:07,977
I need you to look after the kid
for a few weeks or, like, eight.

355
00:21:08,144 --> 00:21:12,189
- I want half that money.
- Are we back to this again?

356
00:21:12,857 --> 00:21:14,567
Is there a real robot boxer in there?

357
00:21:14,733 --> 00:21:16,277
Noisy Boy's in there.
Have you ever heard of him?

358
00:21:16,443 --> 00:21:20,447
Of course. He fought Rubicon
for the WRB belt in 2016.

359
00:21:20,614 --> 00:21:23,200
- [chuckles]
- [beeps]

360
00:21:26,453 --> 00:21:28,455
Holy crap, he looks amazing.

361
00:21:30,291 --> 00:21:32,334
Well, his composite armor
has been replaced.

362
00:21:32,501 --> 00:21:33,961
Let's see if the insides look as good.

363
00:21:34,128 --> 00:21:37,798
I've watched that fight
with Rubicon like 20 times.

364
00:21:37,965 --> 00:21:39,842
He should have had him
in the third round

365
00:21:40,009 --> 00:21:42,845
but Rubicon got lucky
with a huge right and ended it.

366
00:21:44,722 --> 00:21:45,973
[beeping]

367
00:21:56,734 --> 00:21:58,027
[Charlie] Relax, kid. he's on our side.

368
00:21:58,194 --> 00:22:00,738
- Not funny.
- Kind of funny.

369
00:22:00,905 --> 00:22:02,448
You know he
has voice recognition, right?

370
00:22:02,615 --> 00:22:04,450
- No, he doesn't.
- He didn't in the League.

371
00:22:04,617 --> 00:22:06,493
When Noisy fought in Brazil,
they must have put it in.

372
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,288
Brazilians are crazy about
that talk-to-your-robot crap.

373
00:22:12,249 --> 00:22:13,876
Right, left, uppercut!

374
00:22:17,379 --> 00:22:21,008
Doesn't work.
Right, left, uppercut!

375
00:22:21,175 --> 00:22:23,385
I knew that price was too good
to be true. We got screwed.

376
00:22:23,552 --> 00:22:24,803
Give me a second.
Let me see if I can fix it.

377
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:26,764
God, look how good he looks, too.

378
00:22:26,931 --> 00:22:28,349
Give me two seconds.
Let me look at something!

379
00:22:28,515 --> 00:22:29,767
Why didn't you ask the guy
to have a look at it?

380
00:22:29,934 --> 00:22:31,101
Relax!

381
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:32,269
[speaks Japanese]

382
00:22:34,772 --> 00:22:37,274
Whoa, whoa.
What was that? Was that Japanese?

383
00:22:37,441 --> 00:22:39,735
[speaks Japanese]

384
00:22:42,655 --> 00:22:44,406
Let me see if I can reset him
to English. Hang on.

385
00:22:44,573 --> 00:22:47,409
- How the hell do you know Japanese?
- Video games.

386
00:22:48,619 --> 00:22:50,162
[Charlie] You play video games
in Japanese?

387
00:22:50,329 --> 00:22:52,081
Japanese bootlegs are always better.

388
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:01,131
- Give me that.
- OK, so he's reset to English,

389
00:23:01,298 --> 00:23:03,342
and I found his command matrix.

390
00:23:03,509 --> 00:23:05,010
They have pre-loaded a bunch
of combinations.

391
00:23:05,177 --> 00:23:08,347
- They should be listed here.
- Right.

392
00:23:08,514 --> 00:23:10,975
Uh... Top salvo!

393
00:23:12,351 --> 00:23:15,271
- [laughing]
- What did I tell you?

394
00:23:16,563 --> 00:23:18,274
Gravity One Downtown!

395
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:24,446
[chuckling]
I was due for some good luck!

396
00:23:24,613 --> 00:23:26,323
- You're welcome.
- Thank you.

397
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:29,368
Bailey, help me put him in the truck.
I am going to go and get your money.

398
00:23:42,715 --> 00:23:45,175
- Give me the keys.
- I'm coming with you.

399
00:23:45,342 --> 00:23:46,844
- No, you're not.
- Why not?

400
00:23:47,011 --> 00:23:48,804
Because I don't want you with me, OK?

401
00:23:48,971 --> 00:23:52,766
I'm either coming with you, or you're
fishing for your keys in the sewer.

402
00:23:52,933 --> 00:23:56,020
Your choice.
What's it going to be, old man?

403
00:23:56,186 --> 00:23:57,396
[jingles]

404
00:23:57,563 --> 00:24:01,150
Oh, my God. That was close, wasn't it?

405
00:24:01,317 --> 00:24:02,276
Don't do that again.

406
00:24:02,443 --> 00:24:05,029
- Don't, don't, don't.
- That's scaring you, isn't it?

407
00:24:05,195 --> 00:24:08,032
- Don't do this again? Whoa, whoa!
- Get in. Just get in, will ya?

408
00:24:08,198 --> 00:24:09,199
Give me the keys first.

409
00:24:09,366 --> 00:24:10,701
No, you can wait
till I get in the truck.

410
00:24:10,868 --> 00:24:12,995
Thanks, Big Pops.

411
00:24:18,125 --> 00:24:20,002
[Max] Sweet ride.

412
00:24:20,169 --> 00:24:22,171
[Charlie] Put on your seatbelt
and don't talk.

413
00:24:22,338 --> 00:24:27,009
[engine starts]

414
00:24:30,095 --> 00:24:33,057
[? Eminem: "'Till I Collapse"]

415
00:24:43,359 --> 00:24:45,694
I'm taking all bets!

416
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:13,013
Keep up. Stay close.

417
00:25:14,807 --> 00:25:16,475
Hey, hey, hey!

418
00:25:16,642 --> 00:25:19,103
Charlie Kenton is in the house!

419
00:25:19,269 --> 00:25:20,354
All right, all right.

420
00:25:20,521 --> 00:25:22,606
- [man] Come on, man!
- Hey, Finn.

421
00:25:22,773 --> 00:25:25,818
- Is that Noisy Boy?
- The one and only.

422
00:25:25,984 --> 00:25:30,155
- That's Noisy Boy!
- [cheering]

423
00:25:32,324 --> 00:25:34,827
Noisy's been in Japan.
Softer bots over there.

424
00:25:34,993 --> 00:25:36,245
You sure you want
to fight him tonight?

425
00:25:36,412 --> 00:25:39,498
What do you got, Finn? He can take any
bot in this place. You know it.

426
00:25:39,665 --> 00:25:42,626
[laughs] You can have
any undercard you want.

427
00:25:42,793 --> 00:25:44,128
- Five thousand guaranteed.
- Come on, man.

428
00:25:44,294 --> 00:25:47,297
A thousand
every round your bot survives.

429
00:25:47,464 --> 00:25:49,842
- Fight till the death!
- [crowd cheering]

430
00:25:52,052 --> 00:25:54,388
No. Give me the main event.

431
00:25:54,555 --> 00:25:56,682
- Come on, Charlie.
- Finn, this is Noisy Boy.

432
00:25:56,849 --> 00:25:58,559
An original Tak Mashido bot.

433
00:25:58,725 --> 00:26:01,353
He was a World Robot League boxer.
Come on!

434
00:26:04,148 --> 00:26:05,983
You want to fight Midas?

435
00:26:06,150 --> 00:26:09,278
Fifty thousand guaranteed,
winner takes all.

436
00:26:10,195 --> 00:26:12,239
Fifty? Really, 50?

437
00:26:12,406 --> 00:26:13,615
Now you're talking.

438
00:26:13,782 --> 00:26:15,659
[Max] Listen, listen. No, look.

439
00:26:15,826 --> 00:26:17,453
- Listen!
- Give me a sec.

440
00:26:17,619 --> 00:26:19,455
We should take an undercard fight,
make a little cash

441
00:26:19,621 --> 00:26:20,831
and get the hell out of here!

442
00:26:20,998 --> 00:26:22,374
All right, first, there is no "we."

443
00:26:22,541 --> 00:26:25,669
Second, he's going to crush Midas,
and I'm going to make real cash!

444
00:26:26,795 --> 00:26:28,422
We'll take Midas!

445
00:26:28,589 --> 00:26:31,008
[crowd cheering]

446
00:26:31,175 --> 00:26:34,178
[metal music playing]

447
00:26:36,555 --> 00:26:38,932
Yeah!

448
00:26:40,893 --> 00:26:43,562
Tonight, our main event

449
00:26:43,729 --> 00:26:48,650
features the gold-blooded killer!

450
00:26:50,152 --> 00:26:52,613
This pimped-out punk

451
00:26:52,779 --> 00:26:57,117
is programmed for pain!

452
00:26:57,284 --> 00:27:02,289
I give to you the mighty Midas!

453
00:27:18,347 --> 00:27:19,556
Whoo!

454
00:27:43,247 --> 00:27:46,083
Against a bot

455
00:27:46,250 --> 00:27:51,046
who ran with the big boys in the WRB!

456
00:27:52,047 --> 00:27:57,052
He's been on an exile tour overseas,
but now he's back home

457
00:27:57,219 --> 00:27:59,513
and he's ready to make some noise!

458
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:02,933
Take your first look in a long time

459
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:05,936
at Noisy Boy!

460
00:28:45,809 --> 00:28:47,894
Crash Palace,

461
00:28:48,061 --> 00:28:52,941
who's ready for some destruction?!

462
00:28:54,151 --> 00:28:57,696
Let's make some money! Come on!

463
00:28:57,863 --> 00:29:00,616
[Finn] We have Midas against Noisy Boy.

464
00:29:00,782 --> 00:29:02,993
Noisy Boy against Midas.

465
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:06,371
You've been waiting all night
for this matchup, Crash Palace!

466
00:29:10,959 --> 00:29:11,960
[bell rings]

467
00:29:12,544 --> 00:29:13,754
Scimitar right!

468
00:29:16,965 --> 00:29:18,675
Did you see that?

469
00:29:18,842 --> 00:29:21,803
Easy money, easy money all night.
All night long!

470
00:29:21,970 --> 00:29:25,098
Come on! It's not over yet. Let's go!

471
00:29:25,849 --> 00:29:27,392
Skull salvo! Firefight!

472
00:29:30,020 --> 00:29:32,898
- Yeah! Go, Noisy!
- Undercard, huh?

473
00:29:35,734 --> 00:29:36,818
Shockfist!

474
00:29:40,113 --> 00:29:41,865
Get in there. Shogun Trinity!

475
00:29:43,450 --> 00:29:45,744
Let's finish him. Gravity Slam, Uptown!

476
00:29:49,122 --> 00:29:50,707
This son-of-a-bitch is crazy!

477
00:29:50,874 --> 00:29:52,000
Get up!

478
00:29:53,210 --> 00:29:55,420
Full Metal Feud! Bring it!

479
00:29:59,007 --> 00:30:00,550
Southpaw! Pain Revolution!

480
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,261
I got something for you.

481
00:30:04,471 --> 00:30:08,558
Don't you run from me!
You can't run from me!

482
00:30:09,601 --> 00:30:10,644
Get up!

483
00:30:13,855 --> 00:30:15,273
That's illegal!

484
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,275
This is the underworld, kid.
There are no rules!

485
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,695
[Finn] Now we're seeing
the Midas touch.

486
00:30:19,861 --> 00:30:21,071
No. Hands up!

487
00:30:21,238 --> 00:30:24,324
Get back in that corner, bitch,
and take this whooping like a man!

488
00:30:28,203 --> 00:30:29,788
He's getting killed in there!

489
00:30:32,332 --> 00:30:36,586
It's a headset! You talk into it
and you tell him what to do!

490
00:30:36,753 --> 00:30:38,171
Panic Shield!

491
00:30:39,047 --> 00:30:41,174
That's it. One-Two Overlord!

492
00:30:44,052 --> 00:30:45,137
[grunting]

493
00:30:45,303 --> 00:30:47,597
No, no. Shatter Punch!

494
00:30:52,144 --> 00:30:53,979
- Five Recall!
- Get some!

495
00:30:57,774 --> 00:30:59,651
Jeez, damn it.

496
00:30:59,818 --> 00:31:01,194
Jab, jab!

497
00:31:08,535 --> 00:31:10,287
Right roundhouse! Roundhouse!

498
00:31:10,454 --> 00:31:13,165
[Finn] Did he just spit
his juice in Midas's face?

499
00:31:13,331 --> 00:31:15,834
No, you did not spit in Midas's face!

500
00:31:16,001 --> 00:31:19,755
- It's party time now, Crash Palace!
- Use your left!

501
00:31:20,630 --> 00:31:22,924
[Finn] Noisy's trying to do something
with his one arm!

502
00:31:23,091 --> 00:31:25,719
But Midas pins him,
and Daddy goes to work!

503
00:31:31,224 --> 00:31:33,602
No, no, no! Get up!

504
00:31:35,145 --> 00:31:36,146
Get some!

505
00:31:36,313 --> 00:31:37,773
He's got...
Just gotta get to the bell.

506
00:31:37,939 --> 00:31:40,108
Move! Get out of the corner!

507
00:31:42,611 --> 00:31:45,113
[crowd chanting] Midas! Midas! Midas!

508
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:48,867
Somebody's ready
to serve up a decappuccino!

509
00:31:49,034 --> 00:31:51,953
I got something for you!
You ready?

510
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:56,416
[Finn] Good night!
That's a home run for Midas.

511
00:31:56,583 --> 00:31:59,628
And so long to Noisy Boy.

512
00:32:09,846 --> 00:32:12,224
[screaming]

513
00:32:12,390 --> 00:32:15,811
[crowd chanting] Midas! Midas! Midas!

514
00:32:31,701 --> 00:32:34,579
Well, that sucked. You hungry?

515
00:32:34,746 --> 00:32:36,957
I saved what's left
of Noisy's voice recognition board.

516
00:32:37,123 --> 00:32:39,960
Other than that, he's trash.
I got to get a new robot together.

517
00:32:40,126 --> 00:32:43,547
I need to find a mainframe. What?

518
00:32:43,713 --> 00:32:45,549
- I hate hamburgers.
- What kid hates burgers?

519
00:32:45,715 --> 00:32:48,927
Fine, more for me.
Here, drink this.

520
00:32:49,094 --> 00:32:50,679
You never should have taken that fight.

521
00:32:50,846 --> 00:32:53,557
Really? Really? Thanks, genius.

522
00:32:53,723 --> 00:32:56,476
Do you even think about the stuff you do
before you do it?

523
00:32:56,643 --> 00:32:58,728
You had no idea how to fight that fight.

524
00:32:58,895 --> 00:33:02,399
Those combination codes, you didn't
know what half of them even meant.

525
00:33:02,566 --> 00:33:04,818
You threw them in there cocky
and half-assed.

526
00:33:04,985 --> 00:33:06,736
Of course he lost.
You never gave him a chance.

527
00:33:06,903 --> 00:33:09,489
- He wasn't that good.
- Noisy Boy was a great robot.

528
00:33:09,656 --> 00:33:12,409
Was. Was a great robot back
in the League, back in the day.

529
00:33:12,576 --> 00:33:14,119
But look around you, kid. This place...

530
00:33:14,286 --> 00:33:16,538
This place is where once great robots
go to die.

531
00:33:16,705 --> 00:33:19,291
So throw him away.
That's what you do, right?

532
00:33:19,457 --> 00:33:21,334
Anything you don't need
you just throw away.

533
00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:25,380
Wow.

534
00:33:27,007 --> 00:33:28,008
It's been a long night.

535
00:33:28,174 --> 00:33:31,136
If you want to sleep indoors tonight,
shut up and get in the truck.

536
00:33:31,303 --> 00:33:33,889
Don't look at me like that way.
Get in the truck!

537
00:34:01,249 --> 00:34:04,294
Well, they gave me 400 for his head.

538
00:34:22,145 --> 00:34:24,481
You stay put.
I'm going to go look for some parts.

539
00:34:24,648 --> 00:34:26,232
- I'm coming with you.
- Huh?

540
00:34:26,399 --> 00:34:27,776
That drink has my heart pounding.

541
00:34:27,943 --> 00:34:30,111
If I sit in this truck by myself,
my head will explode.

542
00:34:30,278 --> 00:34:31,738
Whatever. Just keep up.

543
00:34:38,119 --> 00:34:41,957
[thunder crashing]

544
00:34:42,123 --> 00:34:44,250
Crap.

545
00:34:44,417 --> 00:34:45,627
Stay back, stay back, stay back.

546
00:34:56,972 --> 00:34:59,849
All right, keep up.

547
00:35:00,850 --> 00:35:01,977
These searchlights are automated,

548
00:35:02,143 --> 00:35:04,437
but you got to time them right,
so stay close.

549
00:35:05,522 --> 00:35:07,023
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

550
00:35:07,190 --> 00:35:09,943
Keep up. It's all right.

551
00:35:10,110 --> 00:35:12,612
All right. Come on, come on.

552
00:35:13,279 --> 00:35:15,240
- We're going to get caught.
- Come on.

553
00:35:16,241 --> 00:35:18,910
Easy, easy. Easy, easy.

554
00:35:19,077 --> 00:35:23,039
Quick, quick. Down in here! Go, go, go!

555
00:35:26,376 --> 00:35:28,211
Robots are on the east side.
We got to be quick in here.

556
00:35:30,714 --> 00:35:32,215
Once we're through here,
there's no more searchlights.

557
00:35:32,382 --> 00:35:34,175
Quick! Go, go, go!

558
00:35:50,066 --> 00:35:52,318
- Here it is.
- What are we looking for?

559
00:35:52,485 --> 00:35:55,238
Anything. Anything I could use
to put a fighting bot together.

560
00:35:55,405 --> 00:35:56,656
- Hey, look.
- What?

561
00:35:58,867 --> 00:36:01,411
It's so small.

562
00:36:01,578 --> 00:36:04,622
Yeah. That's before your time.
That's a Generation One,

563
00:36:04,789 --> 00:36:07,834
the very first fighting bot.
They wanted them to look like us.

564
00:36:08,001 --> 00:36:09,919
The more human, the better.

565
00:36:10,086 --> 00:36:12,630
Crazy how quick everything changed.
Here, put that in the cart.

566
00:36:12,797 --> 00:36:14,007
What changed?

567
00:36:14,174 --> 00:36:16,051
A good question.
Boxing, human boxing.

568
00:36:16,217 --> 00:36:18,011
- It just faded.
- Why?

569
00:36:18,178 --> 00:36:20,305
Because the money moved on.

570
00:36:20,472 --> 00:36:22,974
People wanted more carnage,
more show.

571
00:36:23,141 --> 00:36:25,351
You had the whole Brazilian
underground,

572
00:36:25,518 --> 00:36:28,354
the Gracies, the Machados,
jiu-jitsu, Muay Thai,

573
00:36:28,521 --> 00:36:31,566
and 1,000 styles in between.
Full-on ground-and-pound.

574
00:36:31,733 --> 00:36:32,859
- Look at this.
- What's that?

575
00:36:33,026 --> 00:36:35,820
- I don't know.
- Not bad. Good spot, kid.

576
00:36:35,987 --> 00:36:39,115
You still had human fighters,
human bodies

577
00:36:39,282 --> 00:36:41,451
so you couldn't
give the people what they really wanted:

578
00:36:41,618 --> 00:36:44,788
true, no-holds-barred violence.

579
00:36:46,664 --> 00:36:48,666
So the next logical step:

580
00:36:48,833 --> 00:36:51,878
get the humans out of there
and let the machines kill each other.

581
00:36:53,171 --> 00:36:55,090
Do you miss it?

582
00:36:56,382 --> 00:36:59,469
- Boxing. Do you miss it?
- Careful.

583
00:36:59,636 --> 00:37:01,137
What? I want to know.

584
00:37:01,304 --> 00:37:02,972
Careful, you're on a cliff.

585
00:37:06,142 --> 00:37:07,102
Whoa!

586
00:37:07,268 --> 00:37:10,605
That's a long way down.
If you fell, you'd definitely...

587
00:37:12,065 --> 00:37:13,525
[Max screaming]

588
00:37:13,691 --> 00:37:17,112
- Charlie!
- Max!

589
00:37:19,364 --> 00:37:21,783
Charlie, help me!

590
00:37:46,182 --> 00:37:48,309
Charlie!

591
00:37:48,476 --> 00:37:50,436
Charlie!

592
00:37:50,603 --> 00:37:52,605
Max! Max!

593
00:37:52,772 --> 00:37:55,316
Max!

594
00:37:56,359 --> 00:37:57,443
Max! Max!

595
00:37:57,610 --> 00:38:01,531
- Try not to move!
- I'm on some sort of robot arm.

596
00:38:01,698 --> 00:38:05,660
Wait! Just easy, easy.
Give me your hand. Nice and easy.

597
00:38:05,827 --> 00:38:08,955
Very slowly. Good. OK, don't look down.

598
00:38:09,122 --> 00:38:12,542
Look at me. Look at me.
That's it! I've got you, Max!

599
00:38:12,709 --> 00:38:14,210
You don't have to be scared. I got you!

600
00:38:14,377 --> 00:38:16,713
- It's so far!
- It's OK. I got you.

601
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:19,215
Give me your other hand.
Nice and slow.

602
00:38:19,382 --> 00:38:21,968
Just give me your other hand
very slowly.

603
00:38:22,135 --> 00:38:24,262
Reach back. Come on. Reach!

604
00:38:25,180 --> 00:38:27,473
All right, look at me.
We're going to do this together.

605
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,392
You and me.
Just look at me.

606
00:38:29,559 --> 00:38:31,603
That's it. That's it.

607
00:38:31,769 --> 00:38:35,315
One... two... three!

608
00:38:35,481 --> 00:38:37,233
[screaming]

609
00:38:37,400 --> 00:38:39,319
That's it. I got you!

610
00:38:39,485 --> 00:38:42,739
I got you. I got you. I got you.

611
00:38:42,906 --> 00:38:46,242
- I got you. I got you.
- [Max panting]

612
00:38:48,953 --> 00:38:51,164
You're safe. You're safe.

613
00:38:55,084 --> 00:38:57,003
All right, I got you.

614
00:38:57,170 --> 00:38:58,463
- You all right?
- Yeah.

615
00:38:58,630 --> 00:39:00,548
Come here. Easy. Easy.

616
00:39:02,383 --> 00:39:03,801
You all right?

617
00:39:03,968 --> 00:39:06,012
- You all right?
- Yeah.

618
00:39:06,179 --> 00:39:07,889
I told you it was dangerous.

619
00:39:08,723 --> 00:39:10,475
Careful. We're still on the edge here.

620
00:39:22,737 --> 00:39:26,282
Charlie, I think there's
a whole robot in there.

621
00:39:26,449 --> 00:39:27,825
So what? Let's go. Come on.

622
00:39:28,910 --> 00:39:30,912
I'm taking him with me.
He saved my life.

623
00:39:31,079 --> 00:39:34,582
He did not save your life.
I saved your life. Let's go.

624
00:39:34,749 --> 00:39:37,085
Could you just bring the cart to the
edge? I'll use the winch to get him out.

625
00:39:37,252 --> 00:39:40,797
You want that piece of junk? You get
the cart yourself. I'm through here.

626
00:40:38,646 --> 00:40:41,774
[wheels whirring]

627
00:41:25,818 --> 00:41:27,904
This is what's left of Noisy Boy?

628
00:41:28,071 --> 00:41:30,198
That's it.
His head does make a nice addition

629
00:41:30,365 --> 00:41:33,034
to the front of the Crash Palace.

630
00:41:33,201 --> 00:41:35,745
- [scoffs] It's not funny.
- Let's get a robot, you and me.

631
00:41:35,912 --> 00:41:39,040
Yeah, good idea. You're broke.
I'm almost there myself.

632
00:41:39,207 --> 00:41:41,751
- You destroyed the best shot you had.
- We'll put one together.

633
00:41:41,918 --> 00:41:44,003
You're brilliant at this.
There's good stuff here.

634
00:41:44,170 --> 00:41:45,713
- No, there's nothing here.
- There is. Look.

635
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:50,259
Charlie, all your junk is... it's junk.

636
00:41:50,426 --> 00:41:52,845
You're not even
in the game anymore, Charlie.

637
00:41:53,012 --> 00:41:54,931
- It's all garbage.
- I heard you. It's garbage.

638
00:41:55,098 --> 00:41:56,849
Don't get loud with me.

639
00:41:57,016 --> 00:41:59,143
- You're your problem, Charlie.
- What's that supposed to mean?

640
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:03,356
I have been here for you a long time.
In the ring, out of the ring,

641
00:42:03,523 --> 00:42:05,608
and the whole ugly spiral down,
and I'm tired.

642
00:42:05,775 --> 00:42:09,195
My father invested everything
he had in your fight career.

643
00:42:09,362 --> 00:42:10,655
We loved...

644
00:42:11,572 --> 00:42:16,786
He loved you like family.
And this is his home.

645
00:42:16,953 --> 00:42:19,622
I'm just trying not to let it die.
That's my plan.

646
00:42:20,998 --> 00:42:22,333
What's yours?

647
00:42:24,127 --> 00:42:25,378
[sighs]

648
00:42:34,178 --> 00:42:35,638
You're done, right?

649
00:42:35,805 --> 00:42:36,973
You're finally done?

650
00:42:37,140 --> 00:42:40,560
Because I sure as hell am, Charlie.

651
00:42:41,727 --> 00:42:43,229
I got nothing left.

652
00:42:45,314 --> 00:42:46,315
All right.

653
00:42:48,568 --> 00:42:51,404
Maybe there's something here.

654
00:42:51,571 --> 00:42:53,948
This robot the kid brought
in last night.

655
00:42:54,115 --> 00:42:55,783
Would you look at it for me?

656
00:42:56,367 --> 00:42:57,452
Please?

657
00:43:00,121 --> 00:43:01,164
Bailey?

658
00:43:06,043 --> 00:43:08,129
I've never seen
anything like it before.

659
00:43:08,296 --> 00:43:10,298
He's Generation Two, but barely.

660
00:43:10,465 --> 00:43:12,425
I found a power cell that fits him,

661
00:43:12,592 --> 00:43:15,845
and I hooked him up
to this old G-2 remote that I had, so...

662
00:43:16,012 --> 00:43:17,972
You can at least move him around,
Charlie, but he's crap.

663
00:43:18,139 --> 00:43:20,975
Maybe I can get a sparring gig for him,
make a few hundred bucks.

664
00:43:21,142 --> 00:43:24,103
- Charlie, stop.
- [Max] It's my robot!

665
00:43:24,270 --> 00:43:27,315
It took me half the night
dragging him out of there.

666
00:43:27,482 --> 00:43:29,066
- He's mine.
- He's yours? Yeah.

667
00:43:29,233 --> 00:43:31,694
But the parts we're
putting in him are mine!

668
00:43:32,778 --> 00:43:36,449
You idiots should see if he powers up
before you start fighting over him.

669
00:43:36,616 --> 00:43:37,867
What happened to you?

670
00:43:41,829 --> 00:43:43,414
Hey.

671
00:43:43,581 --> 00:43:44,999
[beeping]

672
00:43:45,166 --> 00:43:47,293
[beeping fades]

673
00:43:47,460 --> 00:43:48,753
[electronic whirring]

674
00:43:54,425 --> 00:43:56,469
Whoa. Whoa.

675
00:43:56,636 --> 00:43:58,346
Watch out. Stay back.

676
00:44:16,739 --> 00:44:19,784
Looks like he's got a shadow function.
That's pretty rare.

677
00:44:20,743 --> 00:44:22,912
He can mime your movements
and store them in memory, Max.

678
00:44:23,079 --> 00:44:25,248
[Charlie] You think there's
anything here we could use?

679
00:44:25,414 --> 00:44:27,250
- [Bailey] Not much.
- There's a bucket...

680
00:44:28,459 --> 00:44:30,419
There's a bucket
I use to wash the truck sometimes.

681
00:44:30,586 --> 00:44:33,464
Use it and clean him up.
He smells like crap.

682
00:44:33,631 --> 00:44:36,551
Wash yourself off, too,
while you're at it. You stink.

683
00:44:36,717 --> 00:44:40,263
I switched him to remote.
It's pretty basic.

684
00:44:40,429 --> 00:44:42,974
Just use the toggles here
to steer him and walk him.

685
00:44:43,140 --> 00:44:45,893
- You play video games, right?
- Of course.

686
00:44:46,060 --> 00:44:48,854
Same idea, only this one's
a thousand-pound robot.

687
00:44:49,564 --> 00:44:50,565
Cool.

688
00:45:24,974 --> 00:45:26,309
"Atom."

689
00:45:33,774 --> 00:45:36,944
[Max] His name is Atom.
Can we get him a fight?

690
00:45:37,111 --> 00:45:38,696
I don't think he
was ever a boxing robot.

691
00:45:38,863 --> 00:45:42,617
He's a G-2, built in early 2014.
He was a sparring bot.

692
00:45:42,783 --> 00:45:44,285
They must have built robots
like this one

693
00:45:44,452 --> 00:45:46,287
that could mirror the fighting style
of any other robot.

694
00:45:46,454 --> 00:45:48,706
OK, so can we get him a fight?

695
00:45:48,873 --> 00:45:51,208
Are you not listening?
He's a sparring bot.

696
00:45:51,375 --> 00:45:54,086
Built to take a lot of hits, but never
dishing out any real punishment.

697
00:45:54,253 --> 00:45:55,838
You could always sell him off for parts.

698
00:45:56,005 --> 00:45:57,298
Can't you get him a fight?

699
00:45:57,465 --> 00:45:59,508
"Why can't you get him a fight?
Get him a fight."

700
00:45:59,675 --> 00:46:01,469
God, you don't quit, do you?

701
00:46:01,636 --> 00:46:04,472
You want me to put him in some
bottom-rung scrap-fest to the death?

702
00:46:04,639 --> 00:46:07,391
I saw how scared you were
at Crash Palace.

703
00:46:07,558 --> 00:46:09,852
The places that would
let you fight this robot

704
00:46:10,019 --> 00:46:11,729
would make you pee your little pants.

705
00:46:11,896 --> 00:46:14,315
Excellent. Get him a fight.

706
00:46:16,359 --> 00:46:18,361
[mechanical chirping]

707
00:46:20,404 --> 00:46:21,364
Stubborn kid.

708
00:46:21,530 --> 00:46:23,491
Surprise, surprise.

709
00:46:47,556 --> 00:46:48,641
[beeping]

710
00:46:56,232 --> 00:46:57,441
[mechanical chirping]

711
00:46:57,608 --> 00:46:59,026
[whirrs]

712
00:47:04,865 --> 00:47:06,200
Let's take a walk.

713
00:47:21,924 --> 00:47:23,175
[Max laughs]

714
00:47:29,265 --> 00:47:31,475
[Atom whirrs]

715
00:48:15,978 --> 00:48:17,396
Can you understand me?

716
00:48:25,362 --> 00:48:28,532
Don't worry.
Your secret's safe with me.

717
00:48:29,408 --> 00:48:31,368
[whirrs]

718
00:48:53,474 --> 00:48:56,018
[Max] You've known Charlie a long time.

719
00:48:56,185 --> 00:48:59,522
Too long.
We both kind of grew up in this gym.

720
00:49:01,440 --> 00:49:02,817
My dad, he trained him.

721
00:49:04,193 --> 00:49:06,654
That's them. That's Charlie.

722
00:49:09,073 --> 00:49:10,991
- [Max] What was he like?
- [Bailey] As a boxer?

723
00:49:11,158 --> 00:49:13,494
- As anything.
- He was something.

724
00:49:13,661 --> 00:49:17,289
He was lean, tough.

725
00:49:17,456 --> 00:49:19,291
No quit, no fear.

726
00:49:23,838 --> 00:49:26,549
Come here.
I want to show you something.

727
00:49:27,591 --> 00:49:31,679
I have this newspaper article
from Phoenix 2007

728
00:49:31,846 --> 00:49:35,432
when Charlie fought Nico Tandy,
the top contender.

729
00:49:35,599 --> 00:49:38,394
- You were at the Nico Tandy fight?
- I was.

730
00:49:38,561 --> 00:49:41,230
Charlie was just supposed
to be a warm-up fight, an easy win.

731
00:49:41,397 --> 00:49:45,025
Nico wasn't
even supposed to break a sweat

732
00:49:45,192 --> 00:49:50,281
but nobody told Charlie that, so he just
kept coming and coming at him.

733
00:49:50,447 --> 00:49:51,782
Check this out.

734
00:49:54,577 --> 00:49:56,495
[Bailey] That's Charlie.

735
00:49:58,038 --> 00:50:00,499
First, Nico couldn't believe
the balls on this nobody.

736
00:50:00,666 --> 00:50:05,129
But Charlie kept coming,
and that's when Nico looked scared.

737
00:50:05,296 --> 00:50:07,131
- Really?
- Really.

738
00:50:07,298 --> 00:50:09,049
He was toying with Nico.

739
00:50:09,216 --> 00:50:12,094
The top contender,
number two in the world

740
00:50:12,261 --> 00:50:15,556
and Charlie was dancing with him.
Pop! Pop! Bam! Pop!

741
00:50:15,723 --> 00:50:18,767
Charlie was floating inches
off the canvas that night.

742
00:50:18,934 --> 00:50:21,770
He was like a ghost.
Nico couldn't even see him.

743
00:50:23,063 --> 00:50:24,064
I could.

744
00:50:27,234 --> 00:50:28,569
He was beautiful.

745
00:50:29,695 --> 00:50:31,030
He was beautiful.

746
00:50:33,824 --> 00:50:36,535
So what happened?
Did Charlie beat Nico Tandy?

747
00:50:36,702 --> 00:50:40,497
No, Nico Tandy put me on my ass
in the 12th round. Twice.

748
00:50:40,664 --> 00:50:42,333
Second time for good. Lights out.

749
00:50:42,499 --> 00:50:44,585
You were ahead on the scorecards
going into the 12th round.

750
00:50:44,752 --> 00:50:47,630
Nico Tandy rung my bell
and went on to be the undefeated

751
00:50:47,796 --> 00:50:49,131
world champ for the next three years.

752
00:50:49,298 --> 00:50:52,009
- So he knocked you out?
- Yeah, so did a lot of guys.

753
00:50:52,176 --> 00:50:53,344
You knocked a lot of guys out, too.

754
00:50:53,510 --> 00:50:55,387
24 and 19.
It's not exactly a career.

755
00:50:55,554 --> 00:50:57,014
But every fight a knockout.

756
00:50:57,181 --> 00:50:59,058
- Yeah.
- Win or lose, fight's not over

757
00:50:59,224 --> 00:51:00,517
- till someone's on the mat.
- Till someone's on the mat.

758
00:51:00,684 --> 00:51:03,187
- Your old man taught me that.
- Damn straight he taught you that.

759
00:51:03,354 --> 00:51:05,606
- [Max] Who else did you fight?
- Go get your stuff together.

760
00:51:05,773 --> 00:51:07,650
I don't need to.
Did you fight for the title?

761
00:51:07,816 --> 00:51:11,070
Yeah, you do.
We leave in an hour. Go.

762
00:51:11,236 --> 00:51:13,572
Wow. Here.

763
00:51:14,865 --> 00:51:16,325
Keep it.

764
00:51:17,660 --> 00:51:20,204
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

765
00:51:24,875 --> 00:51:26,585
I like that kid.

766
00:51:27,544 --> 00:51:28,837
He likes you.

767
00:51:33,884 --> 00:51:37,304
- What I said yesterday was...
- No, nothing more to say.

768
00:51:39,181 --> 00:51:42,142
I'm heading off to Atlanta tonight
to see if I can get a partner

769
00:51:42,309 --> 00:51:43,936
or raise money to get a new bot.

770
00:51:45,187 --> 00:51:49,024
That's what you wanted, right?
Me gone?

771
00:51:53,237 --> 00:51:55,531
Yeah, that's what I wanted.

772
00:52:04,039 --> 00:52:05,040
OK.

773
00:52:14,133 --> 00:52:15,718
[mechanical chirping]

774
00:52:18,012 --> 00:52:19,513
[cell phone rings]

775
00:52:22,725 --> 00:52:23,726
[ringing stops]

776
00:52:38,824 --> 00:52:40,117
Hey. Hey.

777
00:52:41,118 --> 00:52:42,286
Look.

778
00:52:49,418 --> 00:52:51,962
The champ is here. Zeus is here.

779
00:52:52,129 --> 00:52:53,172
Yeah.

780
00:52:55,966 --> 00:52:59,803
<i>[announcer] Zeus! No one has ever</i>
<i>gone two rounds with this monster.</i>

781
00:52:59,970 --> 00:53:01,138
<i>Two rounds!</i>

782
00:53:01,305 --> 00:53:04,683
<i>The champ puts his Real Steel world</i>
<i>championship belt on the line tonight.</i>

783
00:53:04,850 --> 00:53:06,810
<i>He just may have a real fight</i>
<i>on his hands.</i>

784
00:53:06,977 --> 00:53:10,439
<i>Zeus, greatest robot boxer</i>
<i>of all time. Ever.</i>

785
00:53:10,606 --> 00:53:12,232
<i>End of story. Good night!</i>

786
00:53:13,192 --> 00:53:16,487
- So cool. It's so cool.
- What?

787
00:53:18,822 --> 00:53:19,823
[Charlie] Come on.

788
00:53:21,617 --> 00:53:24,578
All right, listen up.
I got to go find Finn.

789
00:53:24,745 --> 00:53:27,539
- I want you to stay in this area, OK?
- OK.

790
00:53:27,706 --> 00:53:30,501
[man] Out of the way. Champ coming
through. Zeus coming through.

791
00:53:30,667 --> 00:53:32,044
Move, move.
Champ coming through.

792
00:53:32,211 --> 00:53:33,545
[whirring]

793
00:53:34,838 --> 00:53:36,548
[reporters clamoring]

794
00:53:42,221 --> 00:53:44,389
[whirring continues]

795
00:53:44,556 --> 00:53:47,643
Farra Lemkova, daughter behind
the father-daughter Zeus team.

796
00:53:47,810 --> 00:53:51,230
They say your father's the money
and you are the mind behind Zeus.

797
00:53:51,396 --> 00:53:53,357
You're very kind,

798
00:53:53,524 --> 00:53:55,442
but I assure you,
the mind behind Zeus

799
00:53:55,609 --> 00:53:57,277
belongs to the great Tak Mashido.

800
00:53:57,444 --> 00:53:59,321
[all clamoring]

801
00:53:59,488 --> 00:54:02,199
What did it take to lure the reclusive
genius, former boy wonder

802
00:54:02,366 --> 00:54:04,201
and arguably the most
important bot designer

803
00:54:04,368 --> 00:54:07,121
in the history of the sport
out of retirement?

804
00:54:08,372 --> 00:54:10,374
Why don't you ask him yourself?

805
00:54:10,541 --> 00:54:11,625
[all clamoring]

806
00:54:15,379 --> 00:54:18,423
Is this Tak Mashido's greatest creation?

807
00:54:19,591 --> 00:54:23,637
Zeus is autonomous and constantly
evolving during a fight.

808
00:54:23,804 --> 00:54:27,850
With his adaptive operating system
he recognizes patterns

809
00:54:28,016 --> 00:54:32,187
and rewrites his fight code
instantaneously.

810
00:54:32,354 --> 00:54:35,691
For myself and Joe Sixpack out there,
are you saying that Zeus...

811
00:54:35,858 --> 00:54:40,696
I'm saying that no matter
what happens in that ring,

812
00:54:40,863 --> 00:54:44,283
the result of any fight is inevitable.

813
00:54:45,450 --> 00:54:46,994
What Zeus sees...

814
00:54:48,495 --> 00:54:49,830
...he kills.

815
00:54:51,373 --> 00:54:52,958
Sweet.

816
00:54:53,125 --> 00:54:54,585
[all clamoring]

817
00:55:02,467 --> 00:55:03,969
[Zeus whirrs]

818
00:55:22,154 --> 00:55:23,405
[Finn] I'm never
going into business with you.

819
00:55:23,572 --> 00:55:25,324
[Charlie] I just need a break here,
Finn. C'mon.

820
00:55:25,490 --> 00:55:27,117
You got that old bot truck out there.

821
00:55:27,284 --> 00:55:29,036
- You always got something in there.
- I got an old G-2 sparring bot,

822
00:55:29,203 --> 00:55:32,164
ain't worth the paint left on it.
What am I supposed to do with that?

823
00:55:32,331 --> 00:55:35,250
The Zoo. Take him to the Zoo.
They fight there tomorrow.

824
00:55:35,417 --> 00:55:37,002
Even I wouldn't be caught dead
at the Zoo.

825
00:55:37,169 --> 00:55:39,880
I just need a little loan. Something...

826
00:55:40,047 --> 00:55:41,673
What?

827
00:55:42,799 --> 00:55:44,468
- You're serious, Charlie?
- A loan.

828
00:55:44,635 --> 00:55:47,721
Something. A couple hundred. Few
hundred. Whatever you got.

829
00:55:47,888 --> 00:55:49,765
You know I'm good for it.

830
00:55:49,932 --> 00:55:54,311
I know you,
and as much as I like you, dude...

831
00:55:54,478 --> 00:55:56,230
...you're a bad bet, brother.

832
00:56:00,150 --> 00:56:01,526
Right, yeah.

833
00:56:08,659 --> 00:56:10,035
[bell ringing]

834
00:56:12,412 --> 00:56:13,622
[crowd cheers at a distance]

835
00:56:13,789 --> 00:56:16,208
- Get back.
- All right. All right.

836
00:56:16,375 --> 00:56:17,876
[electric zapping]

837
00:56:21,380 --> 00:56:23,757
Did you see that?
That's what's left of Axelrod.

838
00:56:23,924 --> 00:56:25,842
Where you been?
I told you to stay put.

839
00:56:26,009 --> 00:56:27,928
You should have seen him.
Zeus was, like, amazing!

840
00:56:28,095 --> 00:56:30,264
- Amazing, huh?
- Unbelievable, yeah.

841
00:56:30,430 --> 00:56:33,433
He was just peppering Axelrod
with punches, but so fast.

842
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:36,228
It was incredible.
Axelrod didn't even land a punch.

843
00:56:36,395 --> 00:56:38,063
He didn't even survive the first round.

844
00:56:38,230 --> 00:56:39,481
Is that what you think boxing is?

845
00:56:39,648 --> 00:56:41,733
Zeus beating up some piece
of steel that they feed him?

846
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:44,653
Axelrod's not just some piece of steel.
And that is what boxing is now.

847
00:56:44,820 --> 00:56:47,406
Deal with it.
And I love it, and I'm in it now.

848
00:56:47,572 --> 00:56:50,367
You're in it now, are you?
You and your G-2 sparring bot?

849
00:56:50,534 --> 00:56:53,954
He's more than that. And if you'd
just get us a fight, you'd see.

850
00:56:54,121 --> 00:56:57,291
You're in luck, kid.
There's a lovely place called the Zoo.

851
00:56:57,457 --> 00:56:58,959
Tomorrow afternoon,
you'll get your fight.

852
00:56:59,126 --> 00:57:01,295
- Great.
- And it will be the end.

853
00:57:02,879 --> 00:57:05,048
I told you I hate hamburgers!

854
00:57:08,885 --> 00:57:10,053
It's a burrito!

855
00:57:18,854 --> 00:57:19,938
[Max] Right uppercut.

856
00:57:23,066 --> 00:57:24,151
Left uppercut.

857
00:57:27,821 --> 00:57:31,658
Bend your knees.
Rise up with both hands.

858
00:57:33,618 --> 00:57:38,457
Again. Bend your knees.
Rise up with both hands.

859
00:57:38,623 --> 00:57:41,960
- You been up all night?
- Yeah. I cleaned him up.

860
00:57:42,127 --> 00:57:44,046
I'm using shadow mode
to program some fight moves

861
00:57:44,212 --> 00:57:45,213
and sync them to the remote.

862
00:57:45,380 --> 00:57:48,633
Yeah. I saw that double-up punch
you were showing him.

863
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:50,927
That's... That's lethal stuff.

864
00:57:51,094 --> 00:57:52,387
Let's do this.

865
00:57:52,554 --> 00:57:55,515
Jeez. Let's do breakfast first.

866
00:57:55,682 --> 00:57:57,517
[rock music playing]

867
00:58:32,886 --> 00:58:34,763
You know you're
bringing him home in pieces, right?

868
00:58:37,015 --> 00:58:38,183
We'll see.

869
00:58:42,854 --> 00:58:44,439
[man laughs]

870
00:58:45,732 --> 00:58:47,776
Let me deal with this.

871
00:58:47,943 --> 00:58:49,277
Charlie Kenton. This is Max.

872
00:58:49,444 --> 00:58:51,321
Kingpin. Call me Kingpin.

873
00:58:51,488 --> 00:58:53,782
- All right, Kingpin, so...
- How much a round?

874
00:58:53,949 --> 00:58:55,617
What's this, we on a field trip?

875
00:58:57,869 --> 00:59:00,247
All right.
He can fight my robot Metro.

876
00:59:00,414 --> 00:59:02,124
I'll give you a 100 bucks
for one two-minute round.

877
00:59:02,290 --> 00:59:03,542
- Take it.
- Three hundred.

878
00:59:03,708 --> 00:59:08,088
One hundred. Baby boy, I'm going to
give you $100 just to get in with Metro.

879
00:59:08,255 --> 00:59:12,259
- How about 500 for two rounds?
- [laughing] Two rounds.

880
00:59:12,426 --> 00:59:14,594
Two rounds, son, he ain't
going to survive one round.

881
00:59:14,761 --> 00:59:17,264
- What if he does?
- He ain't.

882
00:59:17,431 --> 00:59:19,933
Let's just say he does.

883
00:59:21,893 --> 00:59:25,147
If he's still
standing after one round...

884
00:59:26,356 --> 00:59:29,025
- ...I'll give you 1,000 bucks. Shut it!
- A 1,000...

885
00:59:33,113 --> 00:59:34,614
But if he dies in there,

886
00:59:34,781 --> 00:59:36,450
which he will, junior...

887
00:59:38,368 --> 00:59:40,704
...I get to keep what's left.

888
00:59:42,414 --> 00:59:43,707
Take the 100.

889
00:59:44,374 --> 00:59:46,168
Deal.

890
00:59:46,334 --> 00:59:49,004
We're on. We on!

891
00:59:51,715 --> 00:59:53,633
Let's go!

892
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:54,759
[Charlie] You should have taken the 100.

893
00:59:54,926 --> 00:59:57,345
- [Max] I got us a thousand.
- [Charlie] Yeah, if he wins.

894
00:59:57,512 --> 00:59:59,556
[? The Beastie Boys:
"Here's A Little Something For Ya"]

895
01:00:00,515 --> 01:00:02,142
[crowd cheers]

896
01:00:18,033 --> 01:00:19,534
[groans]

897
01:00:23,038 --> 01:00:24,581
You want me to drive?

898
01:00:24,748 --> 01:00:26,291
He's my bot. I got this!

899
01:00:26,458 --> 01:00:29,628
This ain't a video game, kid.
This is for real. Right here.

900
01:00:29,794 --> 01:00:32,964
You said he's coming home in pieces.
What difference does it make?

901
01:00:33,131 --> 01:00:34,299
All right.

902
01:00:36,301 --> 01:00:37,385
I got this.

903
01:00:37,552 --> 01:00:39,763
Let's get it on!
Let's get it on!

904
01:00:39,930 --> 01:00:43,600
Let's get it on
like Ping-Pong in Hong Kong!

905
01:00:43,767 --> 01:00:46,436
Give me a bell! Give me a bell!

906
01:00:50,649 --> 01:00:52,108
[metal music playing]

907
01:00:58,448 --> 01:01:00,742
Don't watch Atom.
Watch your opponent. Watch him.

908
01:01:00,909 --> 01:01:03,245
Watch out for that foot.
He's looking to pin you.

909
01:01:04,704 --> 01:01:07,207
I told you to watch for that foot plant.
Come on.

910
01:01:09,042 --> 01:01:10,669
Here comes the sledgehammer.

911
01:01:15,757 --> 01:01:17,759
Did you see that?

912
01:01:17,926 --> 01:01:20,262
- Come on! Get him!
- Don't yell at him, control him.

913
01:01:20,428 --> 01:01:22,430
Slip right. Back step.

914
01:01:23,139 --> 01:01:25,350
Duck. You're welcome.

915
01:01:25,517 --> 01:01:27,811
- Shut up! You're not helping!
- Actually, I think I am.

916
01:01:27,978 --> 01:01:29,271
No, no, no, no, no.

917
01:01:29,437 --> 01:01:32,190
Backhand. You got speed on this guy.

918
01:01:32,357 --> 01:01:34,109
Just keep moving. Bob.

919
01:01:34,276 --> 01:01:35,318
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

920
01:01:40,615 --> 01:01:42,784
Slip out of that corner.
Keep moving! Bob and weave!

921
01:01:45,036 --> 01:01:46,955
That's it! Now you're listening to me.

922
01:01:56,715 --> 01:02:00,218
He can take a hit. I'll give you this,
kid. Your bot can take a hit.

923
01:02:02,804 --> 01:02:05,307
You better slip that headlock 'cause
this ain't gonna end well for you.

924
01:02:05,473 --> 01:02:06,474
I'm trying!

925
01:02:13,106 --> 01:02:15,275
Thirty seconds!

926
01:02:16,735 --> 01:02:19,321
Thirty se... Half a minute.

927
01:02:19,487 --> 01:02:22,115
Half a minute!
Keep moving! Just move!

928
01:02:25,368 --> 01:02:27,579
C'mon, you've got 20 seconds!

929
01:02:28,330 --> 01:02:30,999
That's a thousand bucks. Twenty
seconds. Let me... Let me take over!

930
01:02:31,166 --> 01:02:32,876
- No...
- Just move, then. Move!

931
01:02:40,008 --> 01:02:41,259
Come on.

932
01:02:41,426 --> 01:02:43,470
Get up, Atom. Get up, Atom.

933
01:02:45,597 --> 01:02:47,766
Count with me! Count with me!
One!

934
01:02:47,932 --> 01:02:48,892
Get up, Atom!

935
01:02:49,059 --> 01:02:51,144
He can't hear you... You know you're
talking to a machine?

936
01:02:51,311 --> 01:02:53,730
[crowd chanting] Four! Five! Six!

937
01:02:53,897 --> 01:02:55,440
Get up, Atom!

938
01:02:55,607 --> 01:02:57,859
All the way up! All the way up!

939
01:02:58,026 --> 01:03:00,445
- No!
- Yeah!

940
01:03:00,612 --> 01:03:02,572
Yes! Yes!

941
01:03:05,033 --> 01:03:06,868
[indistinct]

942
01:03:07,035 --> 01:03:08,828
I'm going to fix it!
I'm going to fix it!

943
01:03:10,664 --> 01:03:12,791
I'm going to fix it! Come on, now.

944
01:03:12,957 --> 01:03:14,584
- This 1,000 bucks...
- Yeah, 1,000.

945
01:03:14,751 --> 01:03:16,586
...double or nothing
he can't make another round.

946
01:03:16,753 --> 01:03:18,296
- Yeah, thanks anyway.
- Deal. Double or nothing.

947
01:03:18,463 --> 01:03:20,674
Baby boy said it!
We're back on! We on!

948
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:23,176
Are you crazy?
You threw away a 1,000 bucks!

949
01:03:23,343 --> 01:03:25,387
He can barely stand up in there.

950
01:03:25,553 --> 01:03:28,014
Look, I really need the money.

951
01:03:29,057 --> 01:03:31,518
I know. Let's work.

952
01:03:33,186 --> 01:03:34,270
Ah, Jesus.

953
01:03:39,818 --> 01:03:41,986
- Watch that. Watch that.
- I got that.

954
01:03:43,530 --> 01:03:44,781
[grunts]

955
01:03:47,033 --> 01:03:49,077
- [whirrs]
- Huh?

956
01:03:49,244 --> 01:03:51,454
- Whoa! Whoa!
- Yeah!

957
01:03:55,125 --> 01:03:58,378
- I got it.
- That's a system failure!

958
01:03:59,379 --> 01:04:01,047
- I don't got it.
- He's going down.

959
01:04:05,093 --> 01:04:07,846
- Yes!
- No!

960
01:04:08,430 --> 01:04:10,807
Start... Hey, hey! Start the count!

961
01:04:11,725 --> 01:04:12,809
Start the count!

962
01:04:12,976 --> 01:04:15,895
One! Two! Three!

963
01:04:16,062 --> 01:04:20,650
[all chant] Four! Five! Six! Seven!

964
01:04:20,817 --> 01:04:22,777
Eight! Nine!

965
01:04:22,944 --> 01:04:24,446
Ten!

966
01:04:24,612 --> 01:04:27,907
You did it! We did it! Wow!

967
01:04:31,453 --> 01:04:33,538
[Max] Yeah!

968
01:04:33,705 --> 01:04:36,291
Time to go. Come on. Grab your robot.

969
01:04:37,083 --> 01:04:40,879
I know, I know!
I know! I know!

970
01:04:41,045 --> 01:04:42,797
Kingpin, pay up.

971
01:04:42,964 --> 01:04:46,009
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I know, I know, I know.

972
01:04:46,176 --> 01:04:49,763
- We owned!
