[Max] Jab.

986
01:06:07,131 --> 01:06:08,633
Jab, jab, hook.

987
01:06:12,637 --> 01:06:14,180
Jab, jab, hook.

988
01:06:17,517 --> 01:06:19,185
I think you have to move your feet.

989
01:06:21,896 --> 01:06:25,900
Your feet. Feet.

990
01:06:39,539 --> 01:06:41,374
[hip-hop music playing]

991
01:07:45,563 --> 01:07:46,981
[Charlie] Nice moves, kid.

992
01:07:49,233 --> 01:07:50,610
How long you been out here?

993
01:07:51,611 --> 01:07:53,237
- Check it out.
- What?

994
01:07:53,404 --> 01:07:55,531
I just spent the night doing
something I think is amazing.

995
01:07:55,698 --> 01:07:58,284
Incredibly amazing.
If it works, you know?

996
01:07:58,451 --> 01:08:00,620
- You know his remote was spotty?
- Yeah.

997
01:08:00,787 --> 01:08:03,581
I killed it. Got rid of it.
We don't need it anymore.

998
01:08:03,748 --> 01:08:04,749
How did you...

999
01:08:06,000 --> 01:08:07,752
I had to start over.

1000
01:08:07,919 --> 01:08:10,505
But I was able
to use the spin frame from Ambush...

1001
01:08:10,672 --> 01:08:14,300
...and take the circuitry sleeve
out of Noisy Boy and it works.

1002
01:08:14,467 --> 01:08:17,679
He knows nothing, but it works.
It really, really works.

1003
01:08:17,845 --> 01:08:18,930
What works?

1004
01:08:20,473 --> 01:08:21,683
I got to turn it on.

1005
01:08:21,849 --> 01:08:23,393
[mechanical chirping]

1006
01:08:24,435 --> 01:08:25,937
Left jab, right uppercut!

1007
01:08:28,064 --> 01:08:29,190
Japan!

1008
01:08:29,357 --> 01:08:31,859
You put Noisy's voice
recognition into Atom?

1009
01:08:32,026 --> 01:08:35,613
- Pretty smart, kid.
- Smart? It could be genius!

1010
01:08:35,780 --> 01:08:38,324
It could be the most incredible thing
in the history of the entire world!

1011
01:08:38,491 --> 01:08:40,410
Easy there, chief, easy. Whoa! Whoa!

1012
01:08:40,576 --> 01:08:43,037
- Did you drink all these sodas?
- I might have had a few.

1013
01:08:43,204 --> 01:08:46,040
- I need you to teach him to box.
- Are you kidding me?

1014
01:08:46,207 --> 01:08:48,918
He's nowhere near advanced enough
to handle Noisy's voice command.

1015
01:08:49,085 --> 01:08:51,087
So he needs your moves.
Your commands.

1016
01:08:51,254 --> 01:08:53,840
- Start over from the ground up.
- Forget it, kid. Forget it.

1017
01:08:54,007 --> 01:08:57,510
You were a boxer, Charlie.
Yesterday at the Zoo,

1018
01:08:57,677 --> 01:09:00,221
you could see things happen
before they even happened.

1019
01:09:00,388 --> 01:09:02,724
I haven't boxed in a long time.
I'm not starting now.

1020
01:09:02,890 --> 01:09:04,434
Who's going to teach him to fight?

1021
01:09:04,600 --> 01:09:07,353
You're doing fine, Max.
You don't need me. Sorry.

1022
01:09:11,774 --> 01:09:13,609
That was really cool,
though, that dance.

1023
01:09:13,776 --> 01:09:16,738
You should do that on Saturday night.

1024
01:09:16,904 --> 01:09:19,782
- Don't make fun of me.
- I'm serious.

1025
01:09:19,949 --> 01:09:22,577
Before the fight, when you guys
take the ring, you should do it.

1026
01:09:22,744 --> 01:09:25,955
There's no way I'm dancing with a robot
in front of a boxing crowd.

1027
01:09:26,122 --> 01:09:29,500
A box... Are you kidding me?
This is just a show.

1028
01:09:29,667 --> 01:09:31,711
People want to see something
they've never seen.

1029
01:09:31,878 --> 01:09:34,589
Look. You think of all the greats.

1030
01:09:34,756 --> 01:09:37,258
Think Ali, Sugar Ray,
Prince Rakim, Gammer,

1031
01:09:37,425 --> 01:09:39,343
