1206
01:21:32,473 --> 01:21:35,309
- [mechanical chirping]
- [radio chatter]

1207
01:21:35,476 --> 01:21:36,810
Duck! Left roundhouse!

1208
01:21:39,563 --> 01:21:40,564
Damn it.

1209
01:21:48,447 --> 01:21:50,282
[Charlie] Lean left! Lean right!

1210
01:21:50,449 --> 01:21:51,992
Cover up! Cover up!

1211
01:21:52,159 --> 01:21:53,160
What's going on in there?

1212
01:21:53,327 --> 01:21:55,162
Too many hits.
He's taking too many hits.

1213
01:22:01,043 --> 01:22:02,336
Get your hands up!

1214
01:22:05,172 --> 01:22:07,007
Get out of that corner! Move!

1215
01:22:10,052 --> 01:22:12,596
Come on, Charlie. He's getting killed
in there! Tell him what to do!

1216
01:22:12,763 --> 01:22:15,474
That guy's got two heads, and about a
foot of reach on us, and no blind spot.

1217
01:22:15,641 --> 01:22:17,434
He's got to have a weakness. Find it!

1218
01:22:23,357 --> 01:22:24,691
Wait, wait, wait.

1219
01:22:25,400 --> 01:22:28,153
Right shoulder, right shoulder,
right shoulder! He's got a tell!

1220
01:22:28,320 --> 01:22:30,823
He's got a hitch in his shoulder
every time he throws that right bomb!

1221
01:22:30,989 --> 01:22:33,116
- So?
- We got him! See? Here it comes again!

1222
01:22:33,283 --> 01:22:35,953
Duck! Spin! Slide left!
Roundhouse! One, two!

1223
01:22:36,119 --> 01:22:39,373
Backstep. Backstep.
Backstep. Lean right.

1224
01:22:39,540 --> 01:22:41,542
Come on, Charlie! Get in there!

1225
01:22:41,708 --> 01:22:44,169
Got to get in close where he can't use
that size and reach on us!

1226
01:22:44,336 --> 01:22:47,506
Left to the body! Right to the body!
Left to the body!

1227
01:22:47,673 --> 01:22:49,007
Yeah, it's working!

1228
01:22:49,174 --> 01:22:51,093
Stay downstairs! Left, right, left!

1229
01:22:52,594 --> 01:22:53,846
These program modes aren't working.

1230
01:22:54,012 --> 01:22:55,264
Left! Right hook, slip!

1231
01:22:55,430 --> 01:22:57,307
Right uppercut! Left uppercut!

1232
01:22:57,474 --> 01:22:59,101
Duck left. Counter right!

1233
01:22:59,268 --> 01:23:01,812
- Get him, Atom!
- Here comes the Charlie Special.

1234
01:23:01,979 --> 01:23:04,982
Three-punch combo
to the body! Out! In! Counter!

1235
01:23:05,148 --> 01:23:07,025
- Two-one-two.
- Two-one-two.

1236
01:23:07,192 --> 01:23:08,610
Stay on him! Lunging right!

1237
01:23:10,404 --> 01:23:11,405
No!

1238
01:23:11,572 --> 01:23:14,074
Don't let him go. Right to the body!
Straight right to the head!

1239
01:23:14,241 --> 01:23:15,617
[rapid beeping]

1240
01:23:15,784 --> 01:23:17,369
[radio chatter]

1241
01:23:19,204 --> 01:23:22,165
- That's it, we got a systems crash!
- Get him, Atom!

1242
01:23:22,332 --> 01:23:24,376
[crowd cheers]

1243
01:23:24,543 --> 01:23:25,377
Damn it!

1244
01:23:25,544 --> 01:23:26,753
This is not happening.
This is not happening, man.

1245
01:23:26,920 --> 01:23:29,298
- Put him away, Charlie!
- Spin left!

1246
01:23:30,299 --> 01:23:31,633
Spin right!

1247
01:23:33,844 --> 01:23:35,762
- Finish him!
- Do it!

1248
01:23:35,929 --> 01:23:37,097
Right uppercut!

1249
01:23:39,683 --> 01:23:40,976
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

1250
01:23:41,143 --> 01:23:43,020
Yeah!

1251
01:23:43,186 --> 01:23:45,898
- Ah! Ah!
- [mechanical whirring]

1252
01:23:47,399 --> 01:23:48,483
He's down!

1253
01:23:49,484 --> 01:23:52,696
One! Two! Three!

1254
01:23:52,863 --> 01:23:55,365
Four! Five!

1255
01:23:55,532 --> 01:23:57,951
- Six! Seven!
- We got him. Stay down!

1256
01:23:59,077 --> 01:24:01,705
He's out! He's out!

1257
01:24:01,872 --> 01:24:03,999
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

1258
01:24:07,794 --> 01:24:08,837
Yeah!

1259
01:24:11,840 --> 01:24:13,634
Corner!

1260
01:24:13,800 --> 01:24:16,762
Corner! Corner!

1261
01:24:18,388 --> 01:24:20,766
Victory!

1262
01:24:20,933 --> 01:24:25,145
[announcer] In a time
of one minute, 47 seconds

1263
01:24:25,312 --> 01:24:29,399
of the first round,
Atom has defeat...

1264
01:24:30,609 --> 01:24:33,320
I want to thank everyone
for coming out tonight!

1265
01:24:35,864 --> 01:24:40,118
Our little bot from the junkyard
got a shot at a League fight.

1266
01:24:40,285 --> 01:24:41,620
How about that?

1267
01:24:42,913 --> 01:24:47,459
And the last thing I want to say
to a special girl who won't be named,

1268
01:24:47,626 --> 01:24:50,587
- Farra Lemkova.
- [crowd boos]

1269
01:24:53,256 --> 01:24:54,216
Whoa, OK, hang on.

1270
01:24:54,383 --> 01:24:55,801
That instead of buying my robot,

1271
01:24:55,968 --> 01:24:57,552
and using your
money to control this sport...

1272
01:24:57,719 --> 01:24:59,429
- [Charlie] That's it!
- Wait, I'm not done.

1273
01:24:59,596 --> 01:25:02,683
Why not give
the littlest guy the biggest shot?

1274
01:25:02,849 --> 01:25:06,645
Seriously, because I bet if you give him
a shot, he'll surprise you!

1275
01:25:06,812 --> 01:25:08,730
Wouldn't you
like to see a little guy get a shot

1276
01:25:08,897 --> 01:25:12,859
- at the Real Steel Championship?
- [crowd cheers wildly]

1277
01:25:14,611 --> 01:25:18,156
I challenge Zeus to a fight.

1278
01:25:18,323 --> 01:25:19,616
[crowd boos]

1279
01:25:19,783 --> 01:25:24,162
Any time, any place, anywhere!

1280
01:25:24,329 --> 01:25:26,665
You name it! We will be there!

1281
01:25:26,832 --> 01:25:28,583
Yeah! OK!

1282
01:25:35,048 --> 01:25:36,967
I'm going to get us that fight!

1283
01:25:39,720 --> 01:25:41,596
[crowd cheers]

1284
01:25:41,763 --> 01:25:43,890
[all chanting] Atom, Atom, Atom...

1285
01:25:45,809 --> 01:25:50,063
[chanting continues]

1286
01:25:54,192 --> 01:25:56,653
[echoing shout]

1287
01:25:56,820 --> 01:25:59,072
That was a ballsy move,
you challenging Zeus like that.

1288
01:25:59,239 --> 01:26:00,741
That's one thing to call it.

1289
01:26:00,907 --> 01:26:02,409
I think a lot of people would
like to see that fight.

1290
01:26:02,576 --> 01:26:05,287
- You're damn right they would.
- You listening to this kid? Jeez!

1291
01:26:05,454 --> 01:26:07,164
- Good fight, fellas.
- Thanks, man.

1292
01:26:07,330 --> 01:26:09,082
- Look at this. Let's celebrate.
- Yeah.

1293
01:26:09,249 --> 01:26:12,419
- All right, 70-30, right?
- Yeah, 70 for me and 30 for you.

1294
01:26:12,586 --> 01:26:14,546
- That's so right.
- That's very funny.

1295
01:26:14,713 --> 01:26:16,923
I told you
we shouldn't have sold him.

1296
01:26:17,090 --> 01:26:20,302
OK. No, no, no.
I remember now. Who's right?

1297
01:26:20,469 --> 01:26:22,721
Say who's right. Say "Max is right."

1298
01:26:22,888 --> 01:26:24,806
All right, all right. All right.

1299
01:26:24,973 --> 01:26:28,351
- We're a good team.
- No, no. Max is right.

1300
01:26:28,685 --> 01:26:31,104
[Charlie] That was unbelievable.
Thank you, Twin Cities.

1301
01:26:33,065 --> 01:26:35,025
- Whoo! All right, we set?
- Yeah.

1302
01:26:35,192 --> 01:26:38,195
- All right, let's do it.
- Charlie boy.

1303
01:26:38,361 --> 01:26:41,656
- Ricky, I was just going to call you.
- Oh, yeah.

1304
01:26:41,823 --> 01:26:44,659
I actually really
was going to call you.

1305
01:26:44,826 --> 01:26:46,453
Don't worry about that.

1306
01:26:46,620 --> 01:26:48,538
That was a heck of a fight.

1307
01:26:48,705 --> 01:26:51,083
Congratulations to both of you.
That was really good.

1308
01:26:51,249 --> 01:26:54,211
It was an amazing fight.
That was a great job, young man.

1309
01:26:55,212 --> 01:26:56,546
- Come on, man.
- What?

1310
01:26:56,713 --> 01:27:00,759
- You serious?
- You thought I was joking

1311
01:27:00,926 --> 01:27:02,594
when I said I'd beat you
within an inch of your life?

1312
01:27:02,761 --> 01:27:05,847
He thought that was a joke.
How about that? It wasn't a joke.

1313
01:27:06,014 --> 01:27:10,185
I got a kid here. And I have your money.
We don't have a problem.

1314
01:27:10,352 --> 01:27:12,979
I'm sure you do, Charlie, but...

1315
01:27:13,146 --> 01:27:16,149
...but I think we know it's about
much more than money, don't we?

1316
01:27:16,316 --> 01:27:18,443
All right. What do you want?

1317
01:27:18,610 --> 01:27:21,613
You want 25, 30? You want 30 grand?

1318
01:27:21,780 --> 01:27:23,323
- I got the money in cash here.
- Yeah, right.

1319
01:27:23,490 --> 01:27:26,618
Let's go! Max, go! Go, go! Run!

1320
01:27:26,785 --> 01:27:30,122
- [Charlie] Run! Come on. Keep up!
- [Ricky] Get him now!

1321
01:27:30,288 --> 01:27:31,581
Run! Come on!

1322
01:27:33,458 --> 01:27:35,210
[Charlie] Get off him! Get off him!

1323
01:27:38,547 --> 01:27:39,548
Come here!

1324
01:27:43,927 --> 01:27:45,095
Hey, Ricky.

1325
01:27:45,262 --> 01:27:46,763
That's his money! Leave him out of this!

1326
01:27:47,389 --> 01:27:48,640
[groans]

1327
01:27:48,807 --> 01:27:49,808
Hey!

1328
01:27:59,192 --> 01:28:00,402
Stop!

1329
01:28:01,236 --> 01:28:02,737
[horn honks]

1330
01:28:03,572 --> 01:28:04,781
Stop!

1331
01:28:04,948 --> 01:28:08,577
Take all his money. Take it all.

1332
01:28:11,204 --> 01:28:13,540
Your friend's a real dirtbag, kid.

1333
01:28:13,707 --> 01:28:15,375
He's my father!

1334
01:28:17,586 --> 01:28:22,215
Well. Looks like a little less
than an inch of your life.

1335
01:28:22,382 --> 01:28:25,302
Well, buddy, that will teach him.

1336
01:28:28,555 --> 01:28:30,724
Whoo!

1337
01:28:30,891 --> 01:28:33,727
Just like old times, Charlie boy!

1338
01:28:33,894 --> 01:28:35,228
Let's go, boys.

1339
01:28:40,025 --> 01:28:41,985
[Max] Charlie.

1340
01:29:01,129 --> 01:29:05,342
[panting] I'm sorry, Max.
I'm sorry. Sorry.

1341
01:29:45,382 --> 01:29:47,342
- What are we doing here?
- Max, just...

1342
01:29:47,509 --> 01:29:49,803
Is it Farra?
She called you, didn't she?

1343
01:29:49,970 --> 01:29:52,472
- We're going to get the Zeus fight.
- Listen, it's not the Zeus people.

1344
01:29:52,639 --> 01:29:55,767
I've been thinking about
all this, and...

1345
01:29:56,893 --> 01:29:57,894
[Debra] Max!

1346
01:29:58,853 --> 01:30:00,605
Max?

1347
01:30:03,650 --> 01:30:05,318
Max.

1348
01:30:07,570 --> 01:30:10,031
It's so good to see you.

1349
01:30:10,198 --> 01:30:12,284
- What is she doing here?
- It's better if you go with her now.

1350
01:30:12,450 --> 01:30:14,911
We get beat up,
so you call her to come and get me?

1351
01:30:15,078 --> 01:30:16,788
He's been beat up.
I told you he couldn't take care of him!

1352
01:30:16,955 --> 01:30:19,499
Yeah. I called her.
Look at us. We're a mess.

1353
01:30:19,666 --> 01:30:21,710
We're fine. She can leave!

1354
01:30:21,876 --> 01:30:24,879
Atom's fighting good.
We can make the money back.

1355
01:30:25,630 --> 01:30:27,424
Charlie, please.

1356
01:30:28,341 --> 01:30:29,592
Just...

1357
01:30:32,595 --> 01:30:35,140
Charlie, we're doing so good.

1358
01:30:37,100 --> 01:30:39,019
Charlie, please, no.

1359
01:30:40,270 --> 01:30:43,356
Don't. Don't. Don't.

1360
01:30:43,523 --> 01:30:46,901
Please. Please.

1361
01:30:51,489 --> 01:30:54,534
Trust me, kid.
It's better this way, all right?

1362
01:30:55,368 --> 01:30:57,954
I know you think you know what's right,
but you don't.

1363
01:30:58,121 --> 01:30:59,956
You're too young.
You don't know.

1364
01:31:00,123 --> 01:31:01,541
Look at me, trust me.

1365
01:31:01,708 --> 01:31:05,086
And legally she has custody,
so what can I do?

1366
01:31:06,171 --> 01:31:07,839
You tell me, what can I do?

1367
01:31:12,510 --> 01:31:14,262
Max!

1368
01:31:23,271 --> 01:31:25,690
I don't want your money, Marvin.

1369
01:31:25,857 --> 01:31:27,942
[Debra] Max, we have our
own swimming pool

1370
01:31:28,109 --> 01:31:32,864
and we have a hot tub and a lot
of super fun toys to play with.

1371
01:31:33,031 --> 01:31:35,533
Do you want to play with them?
It's going to be fun.

1372
01:31:36,451 --> 01:31:37,911
What's going on?

1373
01:31:38,078 --> 01:31:41,498
He won't even talk to me,
so thanks for that, Charlie.

1374
01:31:41,664 --> 01:31:43,249
I'm going to wait in the car.

1375
01:31:45,877 --> 01:31:48,338
You don't want to talk, fine. I'll talk.

1376
01:31:48,505 --> 01:31:50,382
What do you want me to say? I'm sorry?

1377
01:31:50,548 --> 01:31:55,595
You knew from day one what this was.
You decided to take the ride.

1378
01:31:56,262 --> 01:32:00,392
I mean, what? Max, you thought me, you,
and a little robot from the junk heap

1379
01:32:00,558 --> 01:32:03,728
were going to
ride off into the sunset? Come on.

1380
01:32:04,896 --> 01:32:07,190
No, you forgot who I was!

1381
01:32:13,321 --> 01:32:14,739
You deserve better...

1382
01:32:16,199 --> 01:32:17,367
...than me.

1383
01:32:21,496 --> 01:32:23,540
Will you say something, please?

1384
01:32:23,706 --> 01:32:26,167
I tried, OK. What do you want from me?

1385
01:32:26,334 --> 01:32:28,044
I want you to fight for me.

1386
01:32:29,295 --> 01:32:31,089
That's all I ever wanted.

1387
01:32:50,942 --> 01:32:53,027
[mid-tempo music plays]

1388
01:34:23,284 --> 01:34:24,327
[door opens]

1389
01:34:36,464 --> 01:34:37,799
No, don't ask.

1390
01:34:39,300 --> 01:34:41,511
So no Max.

1391
01:34:42,762 --> 01:34:46,391
It's better this way. Marv and Debra
have money. Max is set.

1392
01:34:46,558 --> 01:34:49,477
Did you not see
the way he looked at you?

1393
01:34:49,644 --> 01:34:51,771
Charlie, that's the way
I looked at my dad.

1394
01:34:51,938 --> 01:34:54,315
Even now I would give anything
to have that back.

1395
01:34:54,482 --> 01:34:59,237
Your dad was special.
He was in your corner from day one.

1396
01:34:59,404 --> 01:35:00,989
Me, come on. I blew it.

1397
01:35:02,991 --> 01:35:04,450
I blew it.

1398
01:35:05,577 --> 01:35:07,203
When Max was born I just...

1399
01:35:07,370 --> 01:35:09,205
...freaked out.

1400
01:35:09,372 --> 01:35:11,624
But something
would have been better than nothing.

1401
01:35:11,791 --> 01:35:12,917
I just wouldn't know where to start.

1402
01:35:13,084 --> 01:35:14,252
- Yeah, you do.
- I don't.

1403
01:35:14,419 --> 01:35:15,753
- You do.
- No.

1404
01:35:16,588 --> 01:35:17,880
You do.

1405
01:35:50,872 --> 01:35:52,081
I got to go.

1406
01:35:55,043 --> 01:35:56,711
Twelve-hundred miles for a kiss.

1407
01:35:58,129 --> 01:36:00,506
Worth it. Worth it.

1408
01:36:11,809 --> 01:36:13,519
Go get him, Charlie.

1409
01:36:16,898 --> 01:36:18,316
You sound like your dad.

1410
01:36:40,463 --> 01:36:42,340
Hey.

1411
01:36:46,427 --> 01:36:50,431
OK. Uh, look,
I know you think I abandoned you

1412
01:36:50,598 --> 01:36:53,434
and I guess I did originally.

1413
01:36:53,601 --> 01:36:56,354
- Then you sold me.
- [Debra] Charlie.

1414
01:36:56,521 --> 01:36:59,399
- Hey.
- You have no business being here.

1415
01:36:59,565 --> 01:37:01,984
That's true.
You've got full custody. He's yours.

1416
01:37:02,151 --> 01:37:04,612
And I know I've done
all kinds of wrong by this kid,

1417
01:37:04,779 --> 01:37:06,948
but if you'll let me...

1418
01:37:08,199 --> 01:37:10,326
...I'd just like to
do one thing right.

1419
01:37:13,162 --> 01:37:14,247
Right.

1420
01:37:15,873 --> 01:37:17,625
- Now, where were we?
- You sold me.

1421
01:37:17,792 --> 01:37:21,087
- Right, yeah, that happened.
- Wait, what?

1422
01:37:21,254 --> 01:37:23,923
- Then we had our asses kicked.
- And you slept on a shelf in a truck,

1423
01:37:24,090 --> 01:37:25,383
- and it was awful.
- And dangerous.

1424
01:37:25,550 --> 01:37:30,471
Really dangerous. I mean, I know.
God. I'm sorry.

1425
01:37:31,472 --> 01:37:34,434
That's why you came?
To say you're sorry?

1426
01:37:34,600 --> 01:37:36,936
No. I mean yes. Yes.

1427
01:37:39,856 --> 01:37:41,357
But no.

1428
01:37:41,524 --> 01:37:44,360
No, I came to
tell you that I heard you.

1429
01:37:44,527 --> 01:37:48,740
I got it.
I'm a little slow, but I got it.

1430
01:37:48,906 --> 01:37:53,035
I know you had a bum ride, Max, and I
wasn't there and I should have been.

1431
01:37:54,245 --> 01:37:55,455
I should have been.

1432
01:37:56,581 --> 01:37:58,958
Your mom was...

1433
01:37:59,125 --> 01:38:00,376
She was cool, wasn't she?

1434
01:38:01,919 --> 01:38:03,546
She was.

1435
01:38:03,713 --> 01:38:05,757
She was the coolest.

1436
01:38:05,923 --> 01:38:08,468
Yeah, she was.

1437
01:38:11,637 --> 01:38:13,639
And I'm sorry about...

1438
01:38:15,641 --> 01:38:17,560
...what happened with her.

1439
01:38:19,645 --> 01:38:24,192
And I can't get those years back,
Max, but...

1440
01:38:24,358 --> 01:38:26,986
...but I'm here right now...

1441
01:38:27,153 --> 01:38:30,740
...and if you're up for it,
I'm ready to fight.

1442
01:38:44,462 --> 01:38:46,214
We got the Zeus fight.

1443
01:38:46,380 --> 01:38:50,176
- What?
- No, no, we didn't.

1444
01:38:50,343 --> 01:38:52,970
You got the Zeus fight.

1445
01:38:56,474 --> 01:38:59,727
So what do you say, Debra?
Can we do this one last thing?

1446
01:39:03,231 --> 01:39:04,398
One night.

1447
01:39:04,565 --> 01:39:06,025
One night.
It's all we need. Thank you.

1448
01:39:10,822 --> 01:39:14,742
We'll probably get our asses kicked,
but at least we'll go down swinging.

1449
01:39:14,909 --> 01:39:16,118
Yeah?

1450
01:39:16,285 --> 01:39:17,954
What do you say?

1451
01:39:19,914 --> 01:39:21,999
<i>[announcer] Welcome, everyone,</i>
<i>to New York's Bing Arena</i>

1452
01:39:22,166 --> 01:39:24,460
<i>and the Real Steel Championship Bout.</i>

1453
01:39:24,627 --> 01:39:26,963
<i>Well, Tim, it's the fight</i>
<i>we never thought we'd see.</i>

1454
01:39:27,129 --> 01:39:29,340
<i>Zeus, the undefeated WRB champion</i>

1455
01:39:29,507 --> 01:39:32,802
<i>against the underdog, rising star Atom.</i>

1456
01:39:32,969 --> 01:39:34,887
<i>The champ's handlers</i>
<i>have agreed to fight</i>

1457
01:39:35,054 --> 01:39:37,515
<i>outside the circle</i>
<i>of well-known League bots</i>

1458
01:39:37,682 --> 01:39:41,686
<i>and have decided to give the people</i>
<i>a true David versus Goliath spectacle.</i>

1459
01:39:41,853 --> 01:39:45,356
Now, Tim, help me out on this.
Has the Zeus camp lost their mind?

1460
01:39:45,523 --> 01:39:48,109
The greatest robot boxer of all time
gives a shot at the belt

1461
01:39:48,276 --> 01:39:50,319
to a G-2 named Atom?

1462
01:39:50,486 --> 01:39:54,240
Well, Herb, if you ask Tak Mashido,
Team Zeus has lost their minds.

1463
01:39:54,407 --> 01:39:56,659
[Tim] Now, he may look cool
as he enters the arena

1464
01:39:56,826 --> 01:39:59,829
but he has made no bones about
his disdain for this matchup.

1465
01:39:59,996 --> 01:40:02,790
Our cameras tried to catch up
with him earlier this week.

1466
01:40:02,957 --> 01:40:05,710
Take a look at this clip. Mashido
wouldn't even stop to talk to the press,

1467
01:40:05,877 --> 01:40:09,338
<i>referring only to this fight</i>
<i>as an insult to his creation.</i>

1468
01:40:09,505 --> 01:40:11,591
Now, in truth, Herb, Max Kenton,
Atom's trainer,

1469
01:40:11,757 --> 01:40:13,175
did more
than just challenge Zeus.

1470
01:40:13,342 --> 01:40:14,760
He did so publicly.

1471
01:40:14,927 --> 01:40:18,347
The challenge went viral and
created a PR nightmare for the champ.

1472
01:40:18,514 --> 01:40:20,725
No argument there, Tim.
And I think the Zeus camp

1473
01:40:20,892 --> 01:40:23,853
- knows exactly what they're doing.
- That they do. I mean, come on.

1474
01:40:24,020 --> 01:40:26,939
Giving a shot at the belt
to a nobody from nowhere.

1475
01:40:27,106 --> 01:40:30,276
This "junkyard dog," if you will.
That's a marketing stunt.

1476
01:40:30,443 --> 01:40:33,112
And, hey, judging from this crowd,
that stunt is working.

1477
01:40:33,279 --> 01:40:35,781
[reporters clamoring]

1478
01:40:47,710 --> 01:40:49,128
We can't win, can we?

1479
01:40:50,212 --> 01:40:51,297
We'll see.

1480
01:40:55,384 --> 01:40:57,762
[Tim] As the challenger
makes his way into the arena,

1481
01:40:57,929 --> 01:40:59,889
you can hear
the surge of excitement, Herb.

1482
01:41:00,056 --> 01:41:01,641
[crowd cheers]

1483
01:41:11,817 --> 01:41:14,946
[Herb] Atom has arrived onto
the WRB scene with a vengeance,

1484
01:41:15,112 --> 01:41:17,823
using a style,
some would call it human-like,

1485
01:41:17,990 --> 01:41:20,409
that bot fighting has rarely seen.

1486
01:41:20,576 --> 01:41:22,828
Atom and his pint-size trainer
step into the ring

1487
01:41:22,995 --> 01:41:25,831
and the look on Farra Lemkova's face
says it all.

1488
01:41:25,998 --> 01:41:27,792
Welcome to the bigs, junior!

1489
01:41:27,959 --> 01:41:30,920
I'm giving 1-to-5 odds that Atom
don't make it out the first round.

1490
01:41:31,087 --> 01:41:33,089
Now who wants some?

1491
01:41:33,255 --> 01:41:34,590
[Ricky] I'll take some of that action.

1492
01:41:34,757 --> 01:41:38,928
Hey, there!
I'll take some of that action.

1493
01:41:39,095 --> 01:41:42,223
How's it going... partner?

1494
01:41:42,390 --> 01:41:44,350
Partner?

1495
01:41:44,517 --> 01:41:47,436
That's great. How about a
hundred K deep? Is that funny?

1496
01:41:47,603 --> 01:41:50,439
Hundred K says Atom
doesn't see round two.

1497
01:41:50,606 --> 01:41:52,358
You carrying
around that kind of scratch?

1498
01:41:53,526 --> 01:41:55,778
- Yeah.
- Hundred K?

1499
01:41:56,612 --> 01:42:00,574
Tell you what.
Remember section 101, row C

1500
01:42:00,741 --> 01:42:03,661
and you can bring me my money
right to my seat.

1501
01:42:03,828 --> 01:42:06,998
101, row C? Hundred K?

1502
01:42:07,999 --> 01:42:09,041
You heard me, homey.

1503
01:42:09,208 --> 01:42:10,960
- Homey?
- Right?

1504
01:42:11,127 --> 01:42:12,336
Homeboy!

1505
01:42:13,921 --> 01:42:16,215
All right. Peace out, posse.

1506
01:42:16,382 --> 01:42:17,591
Come on, sugar. Let's go.

1507
01:42:36,861 --> 01:42:38,612
[regal music plays]

1508
01:42:41,532 --> 01:42:43,034
[announcer] Never beaten.

1509
01:42:43,200 --> 01:42:44,160
It's showtime!

1510
01:42:44,326 --> 01:42:46,537
[announcer] Never threatened.

1511
01:42:46,704 --> 01:42:49,582
The king of the ring,

1512
01:42:49,749 --> 01:42:52,960
the ruler of robots!

1513
01:42:53,127 --> 01:42:58,424
Bow down to the mighty Zeus!

1514
01:42:59,216 --> 01:43:01,761
[crowd cheers]

1515
01:43:19,528 --> 01:43:21,113
[whirring]

1516
01:43:24,033 --> 01:43:25,242
Oh, shit!

1517
01:43:31,791 --> 01:43:32,958
That was awesome.

1518
01:43:39,632 --> 01:43:40,800
Come on, let's go.

1519
01:43:47,223 --> 01:43:50,351
Ladies and gentlemen,

1520
01:43:50,518 --> 01:43:53,395
in a bout scheduled for five rounds

1521
01:43:53,562 --> 01:43:56,357
for the World Robot
Boxing Championship,

1522
01:43:56,524 --> 01:44:00,402
in the corner to my right,
the challenger, Atom!

1523
01:44:00,569 --> 01:44:01,654
Showboat!

1524
01:44:06,408 --> 01:44:08,786
And in the corner to my left,

1525
01:44:08,953 --> 01:44:12,081
the undeniable champion
of this universe

1526
01:44:12,248 --> 01:44:15,543
and any other universe
known or unknown,

1527
01:44:15,709 --> 01:44:20,131
the mighty Zeus!

1528
01:44:24,301 --> 01:44:27,221
And now, ladies and gentlemen,

1529
01:44:27,388 --> 01:44:28,722
are you ready

1530
01:44:28,889 --> 01:44:34,145
for Real Steel!

1531
01:44:36,814 --> 01:44:37,982
- This is what it's all about!
- [bell rings]

1532
01:44:38,149 --> 01:44:42,236
There's the starting bell
and we are underway.

1533
01:44:42,403 --> 01:44:45,030
The bots
emerge from their corners.

1534
01:44:45,197 --> 01:44:48,075
Zeus decks Atom,
and he is already down.

1535
01:44:48,242 --> 01:44:50,327
- On your feet!
- [electronic whirring]

1536
01:44:50,494 --> 01:44:53,539
[Herb] Looks like we are in
for another Zeus clinic.

1537
01:44:54,790 --> 01:44:57,084
Referee Matt Geiger
coming in the ring to start the count.

1538
01:44:58,085 --> 01:44:59,128
Get up!

1539
01:44:59,295 --> 01:45:00,504
[referee]...two, three...

1540
01:45:00,671 --> 01:45:04,216
Push up! Stand up!

1541
01:45:04,383 --> 01:45:07,052
[Herb] But look at this.
The little bot's back on his feet

1542
01:45:07,219 --> 01:45:10,306
to get a second blistering attack
from Zeus!

1543
01:45:10,472 --> 01:45:12,808
[Tim] And Atom is down for the second
time in less than ten seconds.

1544
01:45:12,975 --> 01:45:16,437
- He's too strong! He's too strong!
- That's my boy right there!

1545
01:45:18,439 --> 01:45:19,982
Get up and get in the game!

1546
01:45:20,149 --> 01:45:23,152
Come on!
No, please Atom, get up! Please!

1547
01:45:23,319 --> 01:45:26,071
Get up! Get up! Get up!

1548
01:45:27,239 --> 01:45:30,201
[Tim] Once again,
the challenger finds his feet!

1549
01:45:31,619 --> 01:45:32,953
Lean back! Lean back!

1550
01:45:33,120 --> 01:45:35,080
[Herb] Atom's getting pummelled
into the corner!

1551
01:45:35,247 --> 01:45:37,499
- Get out of there, Atom!
- Move, Atom, move!

1552
01:45:39,793 --> 01:45:41,837
[Tim] A demolishing inside shot.

1553
01:45:42,004 --> 01:45:43,214
Get your hands up!

1554
01:45:45,216 --> 01:45:46,800
Hands up!

1555
01:45:47,593 --> 01:45:49,094
Crush that little can!

1556
01:45:49,261 --> 01:45:50,596
Get out of the corner!
Get out of the corner!

1557
01:45:50,763 --> 01:45:52,932
[Herb] Charlie Kenton desperately
trying to command his robot

1558
01:45:53,098 --> 01:45:54,058
out of that suicide corner.

1559
01:45:54,225 --> 01:45:55,559
Cover up!

1560
01:45:58,437 --> 01:46:00,189
[groans] Get your feet under you!

1561
01:46:01,774 --> 01:46:03,776
[Tim] Good night, sparring bot!

1562
01:46:03,943 --> 01:46:06,487
It might have taken Zeus a bit longer,
but he's done it again!

1563
01:46:06,654 --> 01:46:10,074
[Herb] Atom is down for the third
and possibly final time tonight.

1564
01:46:10,241 --> 01:46:12,409
- Stand up!
- [crowd chanting] Two!

1565
01:46:12,576 --> 01:46:15,371
- Three!
- C'mon, Atom, get up!

1566
01:46:15,537 --> 01:46:17,706
- Get up, Atom.
- Get up, Atom.

1567
01:46:17,873 --> 01:46:21,043
- [referee] Six! Seven!
- Get up!

1568
01:46:21,210 --> 01:46:23,754
[crowd continues] Eight! Nine!

1569
01:46:23,921 --> 01:46:26,632
[Tim] I don't believe this!
Against all odds,

1570
01:46:26,799 --> 01:46:28,634
this little bot is on his feet again.

1571
01:46:29,802 --> 01:46:30,844
Come on, Atom!

1572
01:46:34,056 --> 01:46:35,224
He can't survive this!

1573
01:46:39,019 --> 01:46:41,272
- Come on, Charlie!
- Right uppercut!

1574
01:46:42,564 --> 01:46:45,317
[Tim] Atom has landed a punch!

1575
01:46:45,484 --> 01:46:48,153
[Herb] Zeus is stunned as he reels back
from an uppercut

1576
01:46:48,320 --> 01:46:51,323
- that he clearly never saw coming!
- Advance!

1577
01:46:52,199 --> 01:46:54,243
Fade back, counter right!

1578
01:46:54,410 --> 01:46:56,245
Fade back, counter right!

1579
01:46:56,412 --> 01:46:58,831
Right cross! Right cross!

1580
01:46:58,998 --> 01:47:00,749
Right cross! Left hook!

1581
01:47:00,916 --> 01:47:03,794
- Let's go! Come on!
- Take him down!

1582
01:47:03,961 --> 01:47:04,837
Double right to the body!

1583
01:47:05,004 --> 01:47:06,714
[Tim] For the first time
in his dominant run,

1584
01:47:06,880 --> 01:47:10,426
Zeus has met a bot who simply
won't back down!

1585
01:47:10,592 --> 01:47:12,219
[crowd cheers]

1586
01:47:12,386 --> 01:47:15,097
[Herb] The crowd is going nuts!
Zeus gives it everything he's got

1587
01:47:15,264 --> 01:47:18,017
as we reach the last 15 seconds
of round one!

1588
01:47:18,183 --> 01:47:22,354
[Tim] Zeus corners Atom,
going double duty with both fists!

1589
01:47:22,521 --> 01:47:25,441
Downtown, uptown,
as the clock winds down!

1590
01:47:25,607 --> 01:47:28,652
- Hands up, chin down.
- Stay low, stay low!

1591
01:47:32,323 --> 01:47:35,534
[Herb] Only five seconds left,
as here comes that monster

1592
01:47:35,701 --> 01:47:37,286
piston-packed right of the champ!

1593
01:47:37,453 --> 01:47:38,620
[bell rings]

1594
01:47:38,787 --> 01:47:42,875
There's the bell! I don't believe it.
Somehow Atom has survived.

1595
01:47:43,042 --> 01:47:45,627
- He made it!
- [Herb] We will have a second round.

1596
01:47:45,794 --> 01:47:48,255
And the crowd here is thrilled!

1597
01:47:51,383 --> 01:47:53,302
He made it!

1598
01:47:53,469 --> 01:47:56,013
Yeah! Corner!

1599
01:47:56,180 --> 01:47:57,723
We got to get out of here,
darling, come on.

1600
01:47:57,890 --> 01:47:59,933
We got to get out of here right now!

1601
01:48:02,686 --> 01:48:05,064
We got to go this way.
Come on!

1602
01:48:10,569 --> 01:48:11,904
OK, you sit down.

1603
01:48:15,199 --> 01:48:17,659
- Let's go, homey.
- All right.

1604
01:48:17,826 --> 01:48:19,453
I'll be back for you, baby.

1605
01:48:20,579 --> 01:48:22,498
Get your hands off me!

1606
01:48:25,376 --> 01:48:27,920
[Herb] Both corners furiously
working on their bots.

1607
01:48:28,087 --> 01:48:31,298
I tell you, Tim, this crowd came here
tonight expecting a massacre

1608
01:48:31,465 --> 01:48:33,592
but instead they're getting a war!

1609
01:48:33,759 --> 01:48:35,135
- You got it?
- [Max] Yeah.

1610
01:48:35,302 --> 01:48:38,555
- All right. Here we go.
- What is happening?

1611
01:48:38,722 --> 01:48:41,934
He is fully prepared
for all possible contingencies.

1612
01:48:42,101 --> 01:48:45,187
- He will be fine.
- What next?

1613
01:48:46,105 --> 01:48:47,439
Round two.

1614
01:48:48,482 --> 01:48:50,401
[rock music playing]

1615
01:48:55,030 --> 01:48:57,241
- [bell rings]
- [Tim] Round two kicks off,

1616
01:48:57,408 --> 01:49:01,787
and incredibly the challenger, Atom,
is giving the champ a run for his money.

1617
01:49:02,830 --> 01:49:06,542
[Herb] Zeus tosses the smaller bot
across the ring like a tin can!

1618
01:49:10,295 --> 01:49:12,548
[Tim] Kenton working his bot
with a trifecta

1619
01:49:12,714 --> 01:49:15,259
of straight rights
to the champ's dome!

1620
01:49:20,347 --> 01:49:24,351
Toe-to-toe they stand,
trading deafening blows!

1621
01:49:27,438 --> 01:49:31,108
[Herb] Whatever strategy either corner
had cooked up has been destroyed!

1622
01:49:33,944 --> 01:49:37,364
Metal bashing metal.
Steel smashing steel.

1623
01:49:37,531 --> 01:49:40,367
This is a brawl!

1624
01:49:42,494 --> 01:49:43,996
[Tim] The crowd is on their feet,

1625
01:49:44,163 --> 01:49:47,082
watching two machines
driven to kill each other!

1626
01:49:47,249 --> 01:49:50,127
Something has to give,
and it does!

1627
01:49:50,294 --> 01:49:52,045
Atom goes down again!

1628
01:49:52,212 --> 01:49:54,214
[Herb] Lights out
for the junkyard dog

1629
01:49:54,381 --> 01:49:56,341
who put on a heck
of a show here tonight!

1630
01:49:58,510 --> 01:50:01,054
[Tim] And yet again,
Atom rises up.

1631
01:50:01,221 --> 01:50:05,684
Kenton must have hardwired this bot
with the will to go on!

1632
01:50:12,149 --> 01:50:17,029
Midway through round four, and Zeus is
looking to end this thing right now.

1633
01:50:17,196 --> 01:50:18,906
[Herb] The champ
is holding nothing back

1634
01:50:19,072 --> 01:50:21,116
as he cracks open the hurt locker!

1635
01:50:27,080 --> 01:50:29,124
[electronic whirring]

1636
01:50:31,835 --> 01:50:33,587
[Herb] Atom is
stumbling around the ring,

1637
01:50:33,754 --> 01:50:35,547
apparently disoriented and dazed!

1638
01:50:35,714 --> 01:50:37,216
- Hands up!
- What's going on?

1639
01:50:37,382 --> 01:50:38,759
I think the voice recog is shot!

1640
01:50:38,926 --> 01:50:40,093
- He's not responding!
- What?

1641
01:50:43,430 --> 01:50:46,141
[Herb] Zeus has found
yet another gear of violence,

1642
01:50:46,308 --> 01:50:48,227
drilling Atom's midsection.

1643
01:50:48,393 --> 01:50:52,648
- No! Stop! Do something!
- He can't hear me!

1644
01:50:52,814 --> 01:50:54,024
[bell rings]

1645
01:50:54,191 --> 01:50:56,276
[Tim] But the bell sounds,
and once again,

1646
01:50:56,443 --> 01:50:59,112
this little robot
has stunned the world!

1647
01:51:01,448 --> 01:51:04,117
We're done, Max!
He can't hear me.

1648
01:51:04,284 --> 01:51:06,411
This is murder.
We've had enough.

1649
01:51:06,578 --> 01:51:08,956
- I'm disabling the voice recognition.
- So what? He can't hear me!

1650
01:51:09,122 --> 01:51:11,500
- Yes, but he can see you!
- What?

1651
01:51:12,876 --> 01:51:15,587
I'm putting him in shadow mode.
Show him what to do.

1652
01:51:15,754 --> 01:51:18,215
Without the voice recognition,
he'll move even faster!

1653
01:51:18,382 --> 01:51:22,344
- No way. No way!
- Look at them. They are freaking out!

1654
01:51:22,511 --> 01:51:24,346
Rich girl is ripping him
a new one over there!

1655
01:51:24,513 --> 01:51:26,598
Do you know why?
Because they're scared.

1656
01:51:26,765 --> 01:51:28,934
Because Atom can do things
no other bot has ever done.

1657
01:51:29,101 --> 01:51:30,811
- But I can't do it!
- Yes, you can.

1658
01:51:30,978 --> 01:51:34,189
- I can't, I can't.
- Yes, you can.

1659
01:51:34,898 --> 01:51:38,443
Show him what to do.
You have to fight the last round.

1660
01:51:38,610 --> 01:51:43,031
- Don't ask me. Don't.
- Charlie... please.

1661
01:51:43,824 --> 01:51:45,492
I beg you.

1662
01:51:53,500 --> 01:51:54,960
Are you kidding me with those eyes?

1663
01:51:56,795 --> 01:52:00,090
- Damn it!
- Yes!

1664
01:52:00,257 --> 01:52:02,676
I can't believe I'm doing this.

1665
01:52:02,843 --> 01:52:05,345
I know you're in there! I'm not sure
if you're getting this or what,

1666
01:52:05,512 --> 01:52:06,763
but I know you're in there!

1667
01:52:06,930 --> 01:52:09,182
- Come on, Kenton. In or out?
- In. Give me a minute.

1668
01:52:12,728 --> 01:52:17,524
I know you can't hear me,
but you can see me, so watch me!

1669
01:52:17,899 --> 01:52:20,110
Watch... me.

1670
01:52:20,277 --> 01:52:23,822
- You know you're talking to a robot.
- I know. Shut up.

1671
01:52:25,032 --> 01:52:26,700
Watch me.

1672
01:52:27,034 --> 01:52:28,952
An epic battle
being waged here tonight,

1673
01:52:29,119 --> 01:52:31,246
as the fifth
and final round gets underway.

1674
01:52:31,413 --> 01:52:33,081
Come on, Atom!

1675
01:52:42,716 --> 01:52:44,968
[Tim] Wait a second, Herb.
Are you seeing this?

1676
01:52:45,135 --> 01:52:48,221
Charlie Kenton
is shadowboxing just outside the ring!

1677
01:52:48,388 --> 01:52:50,641
[Herb] Tim, it looks like Atom
has a shadow function.

1678
01:52:50,807 --> 01:52:53,435
So, basically,
that means Charlie Kenton

1679
01:52:53,602 --> 01:52:56,563
is fighting the last round
of this fight against Zeus.

1680
01:52:56,730 --> 01:52:58,940
[Tim] Well, I tell you what, it doesn't
seem to be much help,

1681
01:52:59,107 --> 01:53:01,193
because Atom is backed up
against the ropes again.

1682
01:53:03,111 --> 01:53:04,946
Charlie, help him! Fight back!

1683
01:53:05,113 --> 01:53:06,365
Not yet.

1684
01:53:08,909 --> 01:53:13,538
[Tim] Tak Mashido supervising
personally as Zeus hammers down,

1685
01:53:13,705 --> 01:53:17,584
furiously trying
to end this thing once and for all.

1686
01:53:17,751 --> 01:53:20,754
[Herb] I got to tell you,
folks, the champ looks tired.

1687
01:53:20,921 --> 01:53:23,215
This robot
seems to be running on empty.

1688
01:53:27,010 --> 01:53:29,304
I don't believe it.
Atom is taunting Zeus.

1689
01:53:29,471 --> 01:53:33,100
- Switch to turbo!
- [Herb] He's actually asking for more.

1690
01:53:35,018 --> 01:53:36,561
Please do something!

1691
01:53:36,728 --> 01:53:39,147
- Not yet.
- That's right, Charlie. Not yet.

1692
01:53:41,858 --> 01:53:43,318
Nitrous pistons, now!

1693
01:53:46,446 --> 01:53:48,448
Charlie, he's not going
to last much longer!

1694
01:53:48,615 --> 01:53:50,992
- Fight back!
- Not yet.

1695
01:53:51,159 --> 01:53:52,411
Hang in there!

1696
01:53:52,577 --> 01:53:55,622
[Tim] Atom is riddled
with the nitrous-fuelled

1697
01:53:55,789 --> 01:53:59,000
Gatling guns of Zeus's blows!

1698
01:53:59,167 --> 01:54:02,879
[crowd chanting] Atom! Atom!
Atom! Atom!

1699
01:54:03,046 --> 01:54:06,174
[chanting continues]

1700
01:54:06,341 --> 01:54:08,552
Wait him out,
wait him out! Not yet!

1701
01:54:11,138 --> 01:54:13,140
[Herb] Zeus is slowing down!

1702
01:54:13,306 --> 01:54:16,059
Tim, the champ's power core
is clearly depleted.

1703
01:54:16,226 --> 01:54:17,394
Charlie, please!

1704
01:54:19,646 --> 01:54:22,607
- Hey, kid. Now.
- Now!

1705
01:54:25,944 --> 01:54:27,154
[electronic beeping]

1706
01:54:28,447 --> 01:54:29,573
Get in there!
Don't let him breathe!

1707
01:54:31,992 --> 01:54:34,286
Knock that little bitch!
Bust him open!

1708
01:54:43,253 --> 01:54:44,546
Yeah! That's right!

1709
01:54:44,713 --> 01:54:46,006
[electronic beeping]

1710
01:54:46,173 --> 01:54:47,424
Do something!

1711
01:54:48,300 --> 01:54:49,342
Move!

1712
01:54:50,844 --> 01:54:53,180
Override. Switching to manual.

1713
01:54:55,265 --> 01:54:57,976
[Herb] In a shocking move,
Tak Mashido is manually

1714
01:54:58,143 --> 01:55:00,020
operating his robot personally!

1715
01:55:10,572 --> 01:55:12,073
Work the body! Get inside him!

1716
01:55:12,240 --> 01:55:13,241
Get him, Atom!

1717
01:55:14,951 --> 01:55:17,329
[Herb] Look at this!
The champ is trying

1718
01:55:17,496 --> 01:55:21,333
desperately to stay on his feet
but Kenton is relentless,

1719
01:55:21,500 --> 01:55:24,920
landing blow after blow
after blow to the body!

1720
01:56:07,128 --> 01:56:09,297
[Tim] Left! Right! Left! Right!

1721
01:56:09,464 --> 01:56:12,759
A huge uppercut by Atom!

1722
01:56:12,926 --> 01:56:14,761
Zeus is down!

1723
01:56:17,472 --> 01:56:20,475
- Yeah!
- [Tim] This little bot

1724
01:56:20,642 --> 01:56:25,397
has dug deep here tonight
and shown something damn near heart!

1725
01:56:25,564 --> 01:56:29,693
[referee] One, two, three,

1726
01:56:29,860 --> 01:56:34,739
four, five, six, seven...

1727
01:56:34,906 --> 01:56:35,907
He's good!

1728
01:56:36,074 --> 01:56:37,242
[Tim] Zeus gets to his feet.

1729
01:56:37,409 --> 01:56:39,578
[Herb] But Kenton has
Atom on him again,

1730
01:56:39,744 --> 01:56:42,247
landing punch after punch!

1731
01:56:42,414 --> 01:56:44,624
[Tim] Tak Mashido
and his super bot have no answer.

1732
01:56:44,791 --> 01:56:47,752
[Herb] Zeus pins Atom's left arm,
but Kenton is undaunted!

1733
01:56:47,919 --> 01:56:50,171
[Tim] It all comes down to this, folks!

1734
01:56:50,338 --> 01:56:52,173
Drop him, Charlie! Now!

1735
01:56:52,340 --> 01:56:54,384
[Herb] Kenton
is about to drop the champ...

1736
01:56:54,551 --> 01:56:56,386
No! There's the bell!

1737
01:56:56,553 --> 01:56:59,306
[Tim] Zeus is saved by the bell!

1738
01:56:59,472 --> 01:57:02,225
[crowd cheers wildly]

1739
01:57:04,102 --> 01:57:05,353
No!

1740
01:57:05,520 --> 01:57:08,523
[Herb] Amazingly, Tim,
we will go to the judges' cards!

1741
01:57:19,576 --> 01:57:21,703
Now, go on.

1742
01:57:22,037 --> 01:57:25,957
[announcer] Ladies and gentlemen,
after five rounds,

1743
01:57:26,124 --> 01:57:28,793
we go to the judges' scorecards.

1744
01:57:32,756 --> 01:57:37,177
Judge Number One
scores the fight 47-48.

1745
01:57:37,344 --> 01:57:42,265
Judge Number Two
scores the fight 48-46.

1746
01:57:42,432 --> 01:57:47,062
And Judge Number Three
scores the fight 47-46

1747
01:57:47,228 --> 01:57:52,400
for the winner
and still World Robot Boxing champion,

1748
01:57:52,567 --> 01:57:54,945
Zeus!

1749
01:57:56,571 --> 01:57:58,156
[crowd booing]

1750
01:58:00,283 --> 01:58:04,454
Farra... Farra...
Farra Lemkova...

1751
01:58:04,621 --> 01:58:06,957
...you got way more
than you bargained for tonight.

1752
01:58:07,123 --> 01:58:09,334
Some would say
that your bot won the decision

1753
01:58:09,501 --> 01:58:11,086
but lost the fight.

1754
01:58:11,252 --> 01:58:12,629
Oh, she looks pissed.

1755
01:58:12,796 --> 01:58:15,423
It took a little longer
than we thought,

1756
01:58:15,590 --> 01:58:18,927
but the result is as expected.

1757
01:58:19,761 --> 01:58:21,012
We won.

1758
01:58:21,805 --> 01:58:24,683
Zeus is still undefeated.

1759
01:58:27,435 --> 01:58:29,854
Tak... Tak Mashido... Tak...

1760
01:58:30,021 --> 01:58:32,857
Any comment on the absolutely
humiliating near loss

1761
01:58:33,024 --> 01:58:34,651
your bot suffered tonight?

1762
01:58:37,654 --> 01:58:40,073
- Nothing.
- No comment.

1763
01:58:40,240 --> 01:58:41,658
Max. Where's Max?

1764
01:58:41,825 --> 01:58:42,909
Max, let's go, go.

1765
01:58:45,370 --> 01:58:48,081
There he is. Max. Max.

1766
01:58:48,248 --> 01:58:52,293
They're already calling
your bot "the people's champion."

1767
01:58:52,460 --> 01:58:54,963
Yeah!

1768
01:58:55,130 --> 01:58:57,090
Max, what do you say to that?

1769
01:58:58,049 --> 01:58:59,509
People's champion?

1770
01:59:02,095 --> 01:59:03,930
Sounds pretty good to me.

1771
01:59:04,931 --> 01:59:06,516
[crowd cheers wildly]

1772
01:59:09,394 --> 01:59:11,604
Dad? Dad!

1773
01:59:11,771 --> 01:59:14,024
Max! Max! Max!

1774
01:59:15,483 --> 01:59:16,651
- Max!
- Dad!

1775
01:59:24,159 --> 01:59:27,412
Max... Max, I...

1776
01:59:27,579 --> 01:59:29,080
I really want you to know...

1777
01:59:29,247 --> 01:59:31,416
No, I need you to know.

1778
01:59:33,460 --> 01:59:34,544
Don't worry.

1779
01:59:36,087 --> 01:59:37,547
Your secret's safe with me.

1780
01:59:44,637 --> 01:59:46,181
Wait here. Wait here.

1781
01:59:50,852 --> 01:59:52,437
[Atom whirrs]

1782
02:00:00,070 --> 02:00:01,654
[Charlie] Up!

1783
02:00:08,620 --> 02:00:10,371
- [crowd cheering]
- [Charlie] Yes!

1784
02:00:10,538 --> 02:00:12,332
Yeah!

1785
02:00:31,226 --> 02:00:34,729
- Yes!
- Yeah!

1786
02:00:36,106 --> 02:00:38,274
[Charlie] Yeah!

1787
02:00:50,537 --> 02:00:52,956
[♪ Timbaland (Feat. Veronica):
"Give It A Go"]

